deck_excerpt: Shangri-Ira Block ft. Gift Exchange+Angel O7+Mask of Restrict+Closed Forest
deck_description:
(Credit to AceTrainerAJ for his support and decktesting. Much appreciated!)

Some time ago, I made a full zone block deck with Kashtira Shangri-Ira. So, I decided to make a new version, where Supreme King Dragon is going to copycat Shangri-Ira and Rainbow Neos. Rather than using HFD and Raigeki, where you might not be able to destroy everything, Rainbow Neos can get rid of everything your opponent has by shuffling everything into their deck. Oh btw, everything is done within 300 sec, so you can do what I was going to explain in Ranked as well.

 

 

Gameplan

1) When Cthugua is present and Shamisen is in GY, Link Summon Saryuja and Special Summon Gale with it. Then, activate Gale twice to send Shangri-Ira + Rainbow Neos from Extra Deck to GY, at the cost of 6000 LP in total.

2) Place both Predaplants on Pendulum Zones and activate Bufolicula to Fusion Summon Supreme King Dragon by using both Predaplants monsters on Pendulum Zones as materials. Next, activate Supreme King Dragon and target Rainbow Neos in GY to copycat its abilities. There, you can set any spell but combo pieces and send it to GY. This allows you to shuffle all of your opponent's Spells and Traps into their Main Deck.

3) Place ME-PSY-YA on Pendulum Zone and Special Summon Chaos Emperor Dragon with its ability to unlock "Primal Seed" loop. As long as you don't banish Shamisen by accident, all is well.

4) Reset Supreme King Dragon with Book spells. Copycat Rainbow Neos for another time with Supreme King Dragon. There, you can send Panda to GY and you can be able to shuffle all of your opponent's monsters into Main/Extra Deck.

5) Reset Supreme King Dragon with Book spells. This time, gain abilities of Shangri-Ira with Supreme King Dragon. Then, Special Summon Shamisen with its ability.

6) Refill your deck with "Pot of Avarice", in addition to fetching some cards from BZ with "Primal Seed". Then, set Primal Seed + Gift Exchange and Synchro Summon Salamander by using Cthugua + Shamisen as materials.

7) Activate Salamander, which puts every card you have back into Main Deck. Then, play "Gift Exchange" to start blocking your opponent's zones. You should prioritize targeting your combo pieces to fetch them into your hand with "Primal Seed" loop. Here are those:

  • Angel O1: It will be used to reveal Angel O7. There, we can use the ability of O1 to Tribute Summon O7 at the end, by using O1 + Gale as tributes.
  • Angel O7: If Tribute Summoned, Effect Monsters can't activate their effects, wherever they are.
  • Mask of Restrict: Denies tributing for either sides, which blocks Kaiju-related cards.
  • Closed Forest: Denies Field Spells.

8) When all of your opponent's zones are locked with "Gift Exchange" and "Shangri-Ira" combinations, activate "Closed Forest". Set "Mask of Restrict" and Tribute Summon Angel O7. Everything was explained in full detail in #7. Then, set "Primal Seed" and end your turn. Also, ME-PSY-YA allows Spells and Traps to be sent to BZ instead of GY. You can consider it as another blocker, since there are little to none of Spells/Traps that can activate from BZ.

9) During your opponent's Draw Phase, activate "Mask of Restrict". Since your opponent has nothing to do, they will pass the turn back to you. Then, attack your opponent directly to win the game:

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contract Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Into The Void" + "Allure of Darkness" can be found within "The Infinite Void" Secret Pack to save 180 SR!

- "Supreme King Dragon Starving Venom" can be found within "Indomitable Knights" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "Rainbow Neos" can be found within "Crystal Septenary" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "Closed Forest" can be found within "Forest Friends" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "Formula Synchron" can be found within "Stardust Ties" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "T.G. Hyper Librarian" can be found within "Futuristic Creatures" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Lavalval Salamander" can be found within "Combatants of Flame" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Moray of Avarice" can be found within "Treasures of the Cosmic Ocean" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Wonder Wand" and "Spellbook of Knowledge" can be collected by purchasing "Spellbook of Prophecy" deck. 120 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Primal Seed" + "Pot of Acquistiveness" + "Ravenous" + "Gift Exchange" + "Gale Dogra" can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 120 SR and 60 UR!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 630 SR and 150 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. If you have any questions, feel free to ask. Have fun in Master Duel!

deck_excerpt: Just something I threw together with the cards that I have.
deck_description: Trying to cycle through the deck as fast as posible and drop multiple big boys on board.
Final deck
I have no knowledge of how this deck functions

Been playing around with multiple versions of Sylvans. Between 60 card pile Rikka/Aroma/Sylvan I feel like this is the best 40 card version I can currently come up with (totally open to suggestions otherwise)

 

The deck is focused on advantage and recursion. Your main focus of the deck is to get into Sylvan Dancepione as quick as you can to get the excavate highroll. Since most monsters in the deck offer advantage or a way to keep pushing the combo forward it kind of doesn't matter what you hit as long as you hit a single plant at the very least. 

Hitting 3 plants off Dancepione is also completely okay and is most often the absolute best high roll, leading to the best ending board you can make from the sheer advantage you can get. 

The deck also centers around heavily abusing non-HOPT effects, primarily being multiple revivals of Sylvan Hermitree and Aromaseraphy Jasmine/Aromage Jasmine.

The hand fixing this deck can do is absolutely off the charts in my opinion, you should be getting at the very minimum 2 Hermitree draws and 1 Aromaseraphy Jasmine draw for just doing your end board as you would normally taking all other cards out of the equation.

Sylvan Charity is absolutely the best card in the deck even in 2024 now but suffers from sequencing conflicts. Example: You want to Charity first to fix your hand but once you continue that sequence into making Dancepione; you learn you would have benefitted more from holding Charity and taking the gamble on making Dancepione first. But that is why I call this deck Highroll. 

Ultimately, you will see 90% of your cards with any given hand with how many 1/2 card starters there are- compiled with the raw advantage from multiple draws (3+) and searches (Humid Winds, Mardel, Sweet Marjoram, Aromalylith Rosemary).

The most common end board i've managed to land on with this deck with any given hand would look something like:

Benghalancer (1 Bounce, LP loss is irrelevant), Aromalylith Magnolia (Board Protection fusion+ATK boost), Aromage Sweet Marjoram (OPT destroy a card on Life-gain), Teardrop the Rikka Queen (Quick effect tribute an opponents monster), and usually at least 2 of the 3 Dried Winds , Humid Winds , Blessed Winds (Usually you will draw one or two throughout the combo, and search the outlier from Sweet Marjoram if you placed anything other than Humid Winds face up off Aroma Blend)

Thanks for reading, hope you give it a try. If you're interested in a 60 card build honestly throw in the Rikka core and Sunavalon/Therion stuff and mess around as you see fit but I found it didn't help this specific build as it really skews the RNG from Dancepione with that much variance (though summoning Petal or Mudan from Dancepione is pretty sick)

zombie test

This particular list is constructed with both beginner and budget players in mind. If you cannot afford Accesscode Talker, play Borrelsword Dragon instead.

 

A video guide is coming as soon as the written guide has been adequately updated.

 

A link to the written guide, of which an excerpt from is included here, can be found in the comments.

 

"I personally believe that the Fossil Dyna floodgate build is a great pair of training wheels for those attempting to learn the deck. It gives you a clear win condition and combo line: Summon Granite, add Pachy, normal and protect Pachy. This familiarity and linearity allows newer players to focus on developing an intuitive understanding of the archetype.

Regrettably, the simplifiers that make this build good for beginners is also what makes it suffer the most from hand traps. Avramax + Pachy is actually one of the deceivingly strongest boards this deck can produce when left uninterrupted, but also leaves you dead in the water to a myriad of interruptions and board breakers. 

This is why I believe that Fossil Dyna should eventually be abandoned once a player has a rudimentary understanding of the axis on which this Vaylantz operates. The weaknesses of the Granite combo turn from a crutch into a shackle that inhibits player growth, both within the archetype and in general."

deck_excerpt: A reptile based version of Raika I built and am uploading just to be the first person to upload a Raika list
deck_description:
The best possible combo always varies from hand to hand but the basic combo you want to do is send the two Ogdoadics in the deck to the Gy and then revive Nauya using Kamikiris effect after being used for a link summon letting Nauya search you Ogdoadic daybreak. Then you use Nunus Gy effect to revive itself before then tribute it using Daybreak giving you 2 tokens and getting it off the board so you don't get reptile locked. Then you use the tokens and Nauya to either make the link 3 if you have fuel to use its search effect or a second copy of the link 2 and going into Sunavalon Dryatrentiay and searching bloom so that you can negate your opponents entire board on their turn and setting up a potential otk for your next turn.

This is the best build I have found after a few days of testing and I am sure with more testing that better builds will be found that possibly focus on supporting a specific deck to boost the power that Raika already has.

En el primer turno, la opción más eficiente es ejecutar el hand loop mediante Apollo del Motor Horus, aprovechando las habilidades de Coach, The Zombie Vampire y Saryuja para establecer presencia en el campo, la mano y el cementerio.

 

Al iniciar el segundo turno, el mazo cuenta con una variedad de monstruos diseñados para ser agresivos y lograr interrupciones en el campo, al mismo tiempo que despejan la zona de juego.


The main strategy of the deck focuses on the swift summoning of level 8 monsters, aiming to employ Dark World tactics for a 'Hand loop.'

 

During the first turn, the most efficient option is to execute the hand loop using Horus' Engine Apollo, leveraging the abilities of Coach, The Zombie Vampire, and Saryuja to establish presence on the field, in the hand, and in the graveyard.

 

As the second turn begins, the deck features a variety of monsters designed to be aggressive and achieve disruptions on the field, simultaneously clearing the playing area.

Bloody Hell! Or, should I say Lantron? I don't know what to say but I do know how to beat the opponent, so why don't you come along?

 

 

Gameplan

1) Plant three flowers to opposing side with "Black Garden". Then, Special Summon Lantron, either with "Monster Reborn" or Saryuja.

2) Place ME-PSY-YA on Pendulum Zone and Special Summon Chaos Emperor Dragon with its ability to unlock "Primal Seed" loop. As long as you don't banish Ancient + Lantron by accident, everything will be fine.

3) Revive Ancient with "Monster Reborn". Then, Synchro Summon Mefist by using Ancient + Lantron as materials, three times. Then, pass all three Mefist to opposing side with "Mystic Box" by getting rid of flowers and placing them instead.

4) Revive Lantron. In order to defeat the opponent, we have to set a Spell/Trap card and let Mefists unleash their rage, which will be redirected back to opponent thanks to Lantron. Whenever you set, you will deal 300 x 3 = 900 damage in total. To loop, just fetch Field Spells with "Primal Seed" and set them persistently.

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contract Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Monster Reborn" is given for free, if you have completed the tutorial to save 30 UR!

- "Primal Seed" + "Pot of Acquistiveness" + "Ravenous" + "Blood Mefist" can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 150 SR and 60 UR!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 630 SR and 150 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. If you have any questions, feel free to ask. Have fun in Master Duel!

deck_excerpt: Seed Cannon FTK ft. Pineapple + Alich
deck_description:
Hello! In this deck, we will FTK our opponent with a crafty setup revolving around "Seed Cannon". Open fire!

 

 

Gameplan

1) At one point, play "Double Summon" and Special Summon Alich with its ability. "Double Summon" will be used for Pineapple and Alich is going to detonate itself due to its rulings.

2) When Saryuja is present, activate 3 x Seed Cannon. Then, Normal Summon Pineapple and Special Summon Banisher with Saryuja. Finally, Special Summon Black Luster Soldier by banishing Alich + LIGHT to unlock "Primal Seed" loop...

  • If you haven't noticed, ever since Pineapple is present, Seed Cannons are accumulating Plant Counters. Even if you have changed Types of monsters which weren't Plant by default, Pineapple changes the outcome in that regard and starts increasing Plant Counters on Seed Cannons.

3) In order to refill counters to 5, you have to play D.D.R. and target on Alich to Special Summon. Since Alich destroys itself automatically, you can play D.D.R. as many times as you like.

4) It's time to send Seed Cannons to GY and deal damage. Since Banisher delivers everything to BZ, we have to close Banisher with "Book of Moon". Now, 3 x Seed Cannon can be sent to GY to deal 3 x (500 x 5) = 7500 damage in total.

5) Since the damage isn't enough, we have to try again. Open Banisher with "Book of Taiyou" to unlock "Primal Seed" loop another time. Here, play "Soul Release" to banish 1 x Book of Moon + 3 x Seed Cannon. Then, retrieve combo pieces needed with "Primal Seed".

6) Repeat what was explained in #3 + #4 + #5 until your opponent is dead.

deck_excerpt: Superheavy Samurai finally made it to Masterduel! Turn 1.5 cards -> 6+ negates and follow-up!
deck_description:
Historically, Superheavy Samurai has been an obscure rogue archetype possessing interesting unique gimmicks found almost nowhere else - gigantic defense position beatsticks attack while in defense position (applying DEF as ATK), the duelist is rewarded/punished for having no spells and traps in GY, and stealing your opponent's backrow to use as your own. However, with the release of Indomitable Pride, Superheavy Samurai has evolved from a simple beatdown deck into a potent combo machine! 
 
Twelve 1.5 card starters, a link-1 monster reborn and a non-once per turn "ROTA" grant this strategy incredible ability to create monstrous 3 to multiple negate boards, while having tons of follow-up for next turn! The extreme consistency of this deck's starters also give Superheavy Samurai ridiculous amounts of space for staple cards - allowing for 15+ handtraps to be maindecked! This nigh-unstoppable combo juggernaut can play through interruption, multiple negates and smash through Masterduel ladder with the greatest of ease!
 
ARCHETYPES AND DECKBUILDING
 
This version of the deck is played pure, and no other archetypes or engines are splashed in. 
 
There are twelve 1.5 card starters: 3 Prodigy Wakaushi, 3 Soulpiercer, 3 Motorbike and 3 Wagon. Any of these cards + a discard is FULL COMBO! 
 
The amazing consistency granted by the starters grants this deck ridiculous amounts of room for staple cards. Spells and traps cannot be used in this deck since they lock out most of Superheavy Samurai's effects, so the staples are all monster handtraps! In this build, 17 handtraps are used, including the Maxx "C" package (of course, no Called By or Crossout since they're spells and SHS hates spells).
 
40 cards are in the maindeck for maximum consistency and since drawing your garnet 1 ofs isn't too damaging to the combo. Any card that isn't useful in the hand can be discarded as part of the combo as well. 
 
 
COMBOS AND GAMEPLAN
 
Superheavy Samurai plays like full power Adamancipator, Spyral, Drytron and Dragonlink of past formats - build an unbreakable board with abusive not-once-per-turn searches to negate every single play your opponent has. You essentially a FTK board with a million negates everygame. Not only is your board nigh-unbreakable, but your hand likely has 4-6 cards, some handtraps, and some follow-up for next turn's OTK. Even if your opponent breaks your board, you can lean on your handtraps to slow down or stop your opponent. 
 
Here are Superheavy Samurai's main combo and it's variants: 
 
1 Wakaushi + 1 discard = Baronne (omninegate and destroy), Regulus (omninegate), 3-4 material Apollousa (monster negates), 4-6 cards in hand (handtraps + followup)
  1. Place Wakaushi in pendulum scale. Use pendulum effect to place Monk Big Benkei on scale and special summon Wakaushi to field.
  2. Activate Monk Big Benkei's effect to search for Motorbike. 
  3. Discard Motorbike to search for Soulpiercer.
  4. Normal summon Soulpiercer. Link away Soulpiercer for Scarecrow. Soulpiercer searches for Soulpeacemaker. 
  5. Activate Scarecrow's effect and discard 1 card to summon Soulpiercer from GY. 
  6. Synchro summon Accel Stardust using Wakaushi + Soulpiercer. 
  7. CL1 Accel Stardust effect to summon Motorbike from GY, CL2 Soulpiercer effect to search for Stealthy from deck, and CL3 Wakaushi effect to put it on scale. 
  8. Synchro summon Baronne De Fleur using Accel Stardust + Motorbike. 
  9. Activate Soulpeacemaker's effect in hand to equip it to Scarecrow. Activate Soulpeacemaker's effect tributing Scarecrow to summon Scales from deck. 
  10. Scales effect to summon Soulpiercer from GY. 
  11. Summon Stealthy from hand. Link away Stealthy + Soulpiercer to summon Ancient Gear Ballista. 
  12. CL1 Ancient Gear Ballista to search for Ancient Gear Box, CL2 Soulpiercer to search Soulgaia Booster. New chain on resolution, search Infinitrack Tunneller with Ancient Gear Box's effect. 
  13. Activate Soulgaia effect in hand to equip it to Scales. Special summon Soulgaia from the backrow with it's effect. 
  14. Link summon Qliphort Genius using Scales + Soulgaia.
  15. Pendulum summon Ancient Gear Box and Infinitrack Tunneller. Qliphort trigger effect searches for Therion Regulus.
  16. Special summon Therion Regulus from hand by equipping Soulpiercer from the GY. 
  17. Activate Baronne's effect to destroy Soulpiercer that is equipped to Regulus. Search for any Superheavy Samurai from deck (Motorbike for next turn for example).
  18. Link away Ancient Gear Box, Infinitrack Tunneler and Qliphort Genius fora  3 Material Apllousa (Feel free to make a 4 mat Apllousa if you have extra stuff on field).
  19. Activate Infinitrack Tunneller's effect in GY to shuffle back 5 earth machine monsters in your GY (preferably your important 1 ofs like Stealthy, Scales, Soulgaia Booster, Soulpeacemaker and Scarecrow) to draw 2 more cards. 
 
 
Even if your opponent manages to out your entire board, you should have a plethora of handtraps on hand to interrupt and stop your opponent.
 
Going second, the 18 handtraps in the deck SHOULD slow down your opponent enough so that the Superheavy duelist can crack their board. To break an opponent's board the pilot has the options to go for either the usual Superheavy Samurai endboard (which naturally picks apart boards during combo) or for a 4 material Zeus with fieldwipes by summoning two level 4s -> Springans line. 
 
GENERAL TIPS
  • Unfortunately, high impact handtraps like Maxx "C," Droll & Lockbird and Dimension Shifter completely stop the turn for Superheavy Samurai. When that happens, make Bagooska to stall out your opponent until the time is right. 
  • Handtrap your opponent to submission, and when they see your first Superheavy Samurai starter, they generally surrender!
  • Wakaushi/Motorbike's search effect is good bait for a handtrap like Ash. If you have another normal summon Superheavy Samurai starter, you can keep comboing by going into Scarecrow!
  • If you get Drolled, you can also try to summon Wakaushi, discard a card to summon Big Benkei from deck, and synchro summon Masurawo. You get pendulum scales, follow-up searches, potential draw 3, and a 4000DEF hard-to-out beatstick!
 
CONCLUDING REMARKS
 
This critical mass of Earth Machine support plus Soulpiercer's multiple searches coupled with generic Synchro, XYZ and Link boss monsters create a very competent combo juggernaut in Masterduel's ladder ecosystem.
 
Want to reach Masters 1 with a deck that includes 18 handtraps and 12 1 card starters? Superheavy Samurai can do it!

GLHF Duelists!

Not sure if this deck will have some sort of playability for now it's casual. I did borrow the idea of some destiny D.P.E. from someone and if they see it thank you for that idea. Anyone more versed in deck building let me know what inconsistencies or key players I missed or if cutting something might work.

Again, this isn't supposed to be a Meta/Competitive Deck, it's for sure a Rogue Deck but I wanted to share if any other Phantom Knight enjoyers wanted a pure build to have fun. Also any feedback or constructive criticism is welcome!

deck_description:
Welcome! In this deck, we will slowly but surely kill the opponent thanks to "Dark Snake Syndrome" without attacking, which is granted by "Ghostrick Museum". Let me explain!

 

 

Gameplan

1) At one point, play "Time-Tearing Morganite". Then, while "Light Barrier" is active, either Special Summon Arcana with Saryuja or Tribute Summon Arcana thanks to Morganite. Choose the outcome as heads to always skip your opponent's turn at the cost of sending two of your monsters to GY, which is guaranteed of 2 x Cockroach Knight cards later on.

2) Fusion Summon Oracle by using Swirl + Ghost as materials by activating Swirl. Then, if you have played "Into the Void" while holding 2 x Cockroach Knight, activate "Ghostrick Museum" and 3 x Dark Snake Syndrome. Finally, end your turn but don't forget to send two of any monsters but Oracle + Arcana to GY.

3) During the first turn, if you haven't noticed, Cockroach Knights were placed on top of the Main Deck. When your turn begins, you will draw two cards instead of one thanks to Morganite and you are going to draw exactly those Cockroach Knights. Since you are able to Normal Summon or Set twice instead of once, you can place Cockroach Knights on the battlefield. When your turn ends, you can send them to GY with Arcana and skip your opponent's turn. With Cockroach Knights being placed on top of the Main Deck, this step can happen as many times as you want or until the opponent is dead.

4) During the Standby Phase of yours, Dark Snake Syndromes will deal some damage, which will be doubled during each Standby Phases of yours. Although Syndromes deal damage to both sides, thanks to Oracle, what you took will be converted into LP. Thus, you will be immortal while your opponent is going to embrace the death. Also, why bother attacking while "Ghostrick Museum" blocks you doing that and giving your opponent slow and painful death with 3 x Dark Snake Syndromes...

  • If interested, there are other cards which prevent you from attacking your opponent, seen in "Side Deck". Feel free to have a look.

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contract Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

So, in total, you can save up to 570 SR and 120 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. If you have any questions, feel free to ask. Have fun in Master Duel!

deck_excerpt: Coffin Seller FTK ft. Vampire Grace + Dragunity Knight - Trident
deck_description:
Hey, how is it going? In this deck, we will FTK the opponent with "Coffin Seller" thanks to Grace and Trident. Let's jump into action!

 

 

Gameplan

1) At one point, activate "Abyss Dweller" to not be disturbed by your opponent's GY effects.

2) When you have Alector + Grace + Parasite in-hand, discard two of them with Ravenous and Special Summon the remaining one with Saryuja. Mind you, you have to Link Summon Saryuja when you have 4 cards in Main Deck to draw them all and shuffle back all three "Coffin Seller" cards, which is a setup you need to prepare in advance for "The Dark Magicians" (TDM).

3) Place ME-PSY-YA on Pendulum Zone and Special Summon Chaos Emperor Dragon with its ability to unlock "Primal Seed" loop. As long as you don't banish Grace/Parasite by accident, everything will be alright.

4) Fusion Summon TDM by using Parasite + Spellcaster as materials. Activate TDM three times to draw all three "Coffin Seller" Trap cards, which can be activated any time. To reset TDM, don't forget to destroy TDM with "Offerings to the Doomed" and revive with "Monster Reborn".

5) If 3 x Coffin Seller are active, revive Grace and Alector + Flamvell with "Monster Reborn". Then, Synchro Summon Trident by using Alector + Flamvell as materials.

6) Start by sending your opponent's monsters from Main/Extra Deck to GY with Grace/Trident. Each time you do it, you deal 300 x 3 = 900 damage in total, thanks to "Coffin Seller" cards. Since Grace/Trident aren't hard once per turn, you can reset them with Offerings and revive them with Reborn.

7) Repeat what was explained in #6 until your opponent is dead.

deck_description:
Hey! Time to make big brain plays!

 

 

Gameplan

1) Place ME-PSY-YA on Pendulum Zone and Special Summon Chaos Emperor Dragon with its ability to unlock "Primal Seed" loop.

2) Special Summon "Tainted Wisdom". Then, pass it to opponent with "Shien's Spy" but if your opponent's field is full, clear one with Ravenous/Offerings...

  • If discarded via Ravenous/Dugares, use "Monster Reborn" to revive Wisdom.
  • If in-hand, use Saryuja to bring forth Wisdom.

3) XYZ Summon Bounzer by using Stardust + Coral as materials.

4) If Wisdom is in Attack Position, change its battle position with "Enemy Controller", which makes Wisdom in Defense Position. By doing so, mandatory effect of Wisdom will activate, letting you trigger Bounzer to negate and deal 1000 damage.

5) Since neither Bounzer nor Wisdom have hard one per turn effect, we can repeat both as many times as we want to let Bounzer deal 1000 damage repeatedly. As long as you revive Bounzer and reload it with "Overlay Regen", nothing can go wrong.

6) Repeat what was explained in #4 + #5 until opponent dies.

deck_excerpt: Yata-Garasu Lock ft. D.D. Designator + Drop-Off
deck_description:
So, have you heard of infamous Yata-Lock? Ever wondered how to relive but don't know where to start from? Well, you are in luck, as "Treasure Panda" can make it happen.

 

 

Gameplan

1) When Baronne is present, Special Summon Banisher with Saryuja. Then, Special Summon Chaos Emperor Dragon with its ability. Your Primal Seed loop is ready.

2) Play D.D. Designator until you deplete your opponent's resources in-hand. Then, set "Drop Off" to discard whatever your opponent can draw later on. Had "Time Seal" not been banned in Master Duel, you would have used "Temple >>> Time" combo to send signals of Yata-Lock but it is what it is.

3) Play Offerings on Baronne. Then, activate D.D.R. on Baronne. This step is needed to not deck-out besides clearing your opponent's stuff one by one, should you go second.

4) If you have played "Into the Void" and holding "Yata-Garasu" in-hand, set "Primal Seed" and end your turn. On your opponent's Draw Phase, activate "Drop Off". If needed, negate whatever your opponent can activate with Baronne in response to "Drop Off", just in case.

5) When it's your turn, use "Primal Seed" to fetch Yata + Offerings. Then, Normal Summon Yata and attack with it to skip your opponent's Draw Phase. If you also want to skip yours, just destroy Yata with Offerings.

6) Repeat what was explained in #6 besides attacking with other monsters to win the game.

I'm sure there are many other combos! i just can't think of any right now, if you find any let me know we can get stronger together!

deck_name: Power Tool Braver Dragon Prediction Princess
deck_description:
The Red Resonator Predaplant engine for Prediction Princess has a really easy time making Ultimaya Tzolkin since we can easily make Ib the World Chalice Justiciar who not only searches us World Legacy Monstrosity but is also a Level 5 Tuner. And considering that we can use Predaplant Darlingtonia Cobra to search for Ultra Polymerization, we can make Predaplant Ambulomelides which is a Level 5 monster. Ib and Ambulomelides together fulfill Tzolkin's Summoning Conditions of 2 Level 5 or higher monsters  with the same Level including a Tuner and a non-Tuner. And considering that Tzolkin can Special Summon a Level 7 or 8 Dragon Synchro Monster or a Power Tool Synchro Monster when a Spell/Trap is sent on your field, you can get yourself a copy of Power Tool Braver Dragon from your Extra Deck. Power Tool Braver Dragon is a Level 9 EARTH Machine Synchro Monster. On Special Summon, it can equip up to 3 Equip Spells with different names from your Deck and/or GY to it and during the Main Phase, it can Quick Effect send an Equip Spell equipped to itself to the GY to target an Effect Monster on the field and either change its battle position or negate its effects until the end of the turn. It's the same 2.5-card combo you keep seeing to get everything in place: Red Resonator, Predaplant Ophrys Scorpio, and a monster to send from hand to GY. Normal Red Resonator and use it to Special Summon Scorpio from hand. Scorpio sends a monster from hand to GY to Special Summon Predaplant Darlingtonia Cobra from Deck. Cobra triggers to add Ultra Polymerization from Deck to hand. Pay 2000 LP to Fuse Cobra and Scorpio into Predaplant Ambulomelides. Ambulo on Fusion Summon adds a copy of Predapruning from Deck to hand. Banish Ultra Poly from GY targeting Ambulo to Special Summon Cobra and Scorpio back from the GY. Ambulo effect to Tribute Cobra to Special Summon Predaplant Banksiogre from Deck. Synchro Red Resonator and Scorpio into Ib the World Chalice Justiciar who searches World Legacy Monstrosity from Deck on Synchro Summon. Send Ib and Ambulo to GY to Special Summon Ultimaya Tzolken from Extra Deck. Set Predapruning from hand which triggers Tzolkin to Special Summon Power Tool Braver Dragon from Extra Deck. Now, we can do two different things here. We can not activate the effect of Braver Dragon and activate Monstrosity targeting it to get Mardel, Generaider Boss of Light and Thunder King, the Lightningstrike Kaiju from Deck to overlay into Mereologic Aggregator, sending Herald of the Arc Light from Extra Deck to GY for Ritual searches and go through our whole Prediction Princess combo before activating your set Predapruning to bring back either Cobra or Scorpio and Synchroing them with Banksiogre into Cloudcastle who brings back a Level 9 for you to Xyz into Laevateinn, Generaider Boss of Shadows to be a part of your endboard. Or, we can activate Braver Dragon's effect to equip Life Extreme, Metalsilver Armor, and Fleuret de Fleur from Deck to it. Then we activate our set Predapruuning to bring back Cobra or Scorpio and Synchro it and Banksiogre into Cloudcastle, activate Monstrosity targeting Cloudcastle to get Prediction Princess Bibliomuse and another Level 9 from Deck and go through our Prediction Princess combo with Bibliomuse access while having Power Tool Braver Dragon as interruption as part of our endboard. I like this better than the first option because this actually gets us to Bibliomuse, but do what you want. Not too much of an inspired Deck, but it does work and it is nice to have a monster like Power Tool Braver Dragon being part of your series of interruptions. I think that it is a pretty cool monster.

For the Main Deck Monsters: 3 Prediction Princess Tarotrei, 1 Prediction Princess Tarotreith, and 3 Prediction Princess Bibliomuse. Tarotrei can Quick Effect flip a monster on field face-up or face-down and she can Special Summon a Flip Monster from hand or GY face-down during your End Phase. Tarotreith must either be Ritual Summoned or Special Summoned via Tarotrei's effect in the End Phase. Her Flip Effect Special Summons a Flip Monster from your Deck face-downn and she can also Quick Effect flip any number of your monsters face-up or face-down. Bibliomuse can Special Summon herself back face-down after being Tributed and sent there. Her Flip Effect adds a Prediction Princess monster other than herself and a Ritual Spell from Deck to hand and while she is face-up on the field, your Ritual Monsters gain targeting and destruction protection from your opponent’s card effects. 1 Mardel, Generaider Boss of Light as a Level 9 monster that we can Summon off of Monstrosity or get off of Lonefire Blossom to act as a Level 9 target on field for Monstrosity. On Summon, it can add a Generaider card or a Plant monster from Deck to hand. 2 Thunder King, the Lightningstrike Kaiju as Monstrosity targets in Deck and they are Kaijus for Tribute-based removal in general. 1 Predaplant Banksiogre. If anything, we are just using this as a Level 6 Predaplant Tuner that we can get from Deck with Predaplant Ambulomelides. However, it is important to note that it has a mandatory effect that activates when it is sent from the field to the GY that places a Predator Counter on each face-up monster your opponent controls, making their Levels become 1 if they are Level is 2 or higher. 3 Predaplant Ophrys Scorpio which sends a monster from hand to GY on Normal or Special Summon in order to Special Summon a Predaplant from Deck other than itself. 1 Predaplant Darlingtonia Cobra which adds a Fusion or Polymerization Spell Card from Deck to hand if it is Special Summoned by the effect of a Predaplant monster once per Duel. 2 Lonefire Blossom which Tributes a Plant to Special Summon a Plant from Deck. 3 Red Resonator which Special Summons a Level 4 or lower monster from hand on Normal Summon and targets a face-up monster on field and increases your Life Points by the ATK of that monster on Special Summon. And finally, 3 Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring. 

For Spell/Traps: 1 Instant Fusion for Master of Ham. 3 Pot of Prosperity. 1 Ultra Polymerization which pays 2000 LP to Fusion Summon using 2 monsters you control where neither player can activate cards or effects in response to the activation and you can banish it from GY to target a Fusion Monster that was Summoned by its effect to Special Summon the monsters used for its Summon from GY with their effects negated and ATK/DEF changed to 0. 3 Underworld Ritual of Prediction which Ritual Summons a Prediction Princess Ritual Monster from hand or GY face-up or face-down. And you can banish it from GY during the Standby Phase to Special Summon a non-Ritual Prediction Princess monster from Deck face-down. 1 World Legacy Monstrosity which either Special Summons a Level 9 monster from hand or targets a Level 9 monster you control to Special Summon 2 Level 9 monsters from your Deck with a different Type and Attribute but with different names. 1 World Legacy Succession which Special Summons a monster from GY to Linkpoint. 1 Predapruning which Special Summons a Predaplant from GY and equips it with this card. 1 Fleuret de Fleur which can target a Level 2 or lower monster in GY and Special Summon it and equip it with this card but its effects are negated. But we are mainly using it to equip to Power Tool Braver Dragon since if it is sent from the Spell/Trap Zone to the GY, you can equip it to a Synchro Monster you control. 1 Metalsilver Armor which is an Equip Spell that prevents your opponent from targeting monsters on the field, in either GY, or that are banished with card effects except for the equipped monster. This also applies to their monsters, so it can prevent some of your opponent’s effects. 1 Life Extreme which equips only to an EARTH Synchro monster and if it battles, it decreases the opponent’s monster’s ATK by 1500 during damage calc only. And if a monster’s battle position is changed, you can target and destroy a card on field. This is pretty nice when it comes to a Flip Monster Deck. We are not using the effect to Tribute a Power Tool Synchro Monster to Special Summon a Life Stream Dragon from Extra Deck because it literally quite frankly does nothing to help us and it is not like that is the reason why we are even playing this card in the first place. And finally, 1 Angelica’s Angelic Ring which you can only equip to a monster that is equipped with an Equip Card. Each turn, it negates your opponent’s first Spell Card or effect that resolves and while it is equipped, you can gain 500 LP and destroy it in order to have the monster become untargetable by  your opponent’s card effects while it is face-up in the Monster Zone. 

Extra Deck: 1 Master of Ham which Special Summons a Flip Monster from hand or Deck on Fusion Summon. 1 Predaplant Ambulomelides which adds a Predap card on Fusion Summon and can target and Tribute a monster to Special Summon a Predaplant monster from your Deck. 1 Ultimaya Tzolkin which cannot be Synchro Summoned and can only be Special Summoned from Extra Deck by sending 2 Level 5 or higher monsters you control with the same Level including a Tuner and a non-Tuner to the GY. As a soft once per turn, when a Spell/Trap(s) is set on your field, you can Special Summon a Power Tool Synchro Monster or a Level 7 or 8 Dragon Synchro Monster from your Extra Deck. We are using this to get to Power Tool Braver Dragon, but if you theoretically sided in Kaku you can get another Dragon Synchro from Extra Deck like Crystal Wing Synchro Dragon if you really wanted to since Kaku would be acting as our Level 9 Monster on field to target with Monstrosity. But that is up to you, whether or not you want to play a target in Extra Deck for that situation. 1 Cloudcastle which Special Summons a Level 9 monster from your GY on Synchro Summon. 1 Power Tool Braver Dragon. 1 Ib the World Chalice Justiciar which adds a World Legacy card from Deck to hand on Synchro Summon. 2 Herald of the Arc Light which searches for a Ritual Monster or Ritual Spell if sent to the GY. 2 Mereologic Aggregator. 1 Laevateinn, Generaider Boss of Shadows and 1 Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity. 1 S:P Little Knight, 1 I:P Masquerena, and 1 Gravity Controller.

Side Deck: 3 Nibiru, the Primal Being, 2 Gizmek Kaku, the Supreme Shining Sky Stag, 1 Kurikara Divincarnate, 3 Dark Ruler No More, 3 Evenly Matched, and 3 Infinite Impermanence.
Adventurer plunder patroll

Actually Hard Summoning Dante, Pilgrim of the Burning Abyss
deck_description:
I guess that we are looking at 2 Level 9 monsters today: Dante, Pilgrim of the Burning Abyss and Guardian Chimera. Dante is a LIGHT Fairy Fusion Monster that requires 3 Burning Abyss monsters with different names as Fusion Material and must be Fusion Summoned and cannot be Special Summoned by other ways. It cannot be targeted and as a soft once per turn during either player’s turn, he can send a Burning Abyss monster from hand to GY to draw a card and if he is destroyed by battle and sent to GY or sent to GY by your opponent’s card effect, you can send a random card from your opponent’s hand to the GY. Guardian Chimera is a DARK Beast Fusion Monster that must be Fusion Summoned using 3 monsters with different names from your hand and field with at least 1 monster from each location. If it is Fusion Summoned by a Spell Card or effect, you can draw cards equal to the number of cards you fused from hand and pop cards your opponent controls equal to the number of cards fused from the field. And while Polymerization is in your GY, it cannot be targeted by your opponent’s card effects. I decided to play these 2 together because we actually do need Polymerization in our combo to Summon Dante, so having access to an untargetable Chimera with pops is pretty nice to go along with it. And it’s a good thing that Burning Abyss has Level 3 and 3-axis monsters because I wouldn’t know where to even go with this Deck if I wasn’t able to play the Predaplant engine. We are using the Red Resonator and Predaplant Ophrys Scorpio combo from Ib Ham Prediction Princess to facilitate both World Legacy Monstrosity and Fusion Dante, but we are searching for Ultra Polymerization to go into Predaplant Ambulomelides. That means that we still need a way to actually fuse into Dante, Pilgrim of the Burning Abyss. We can’t really search for The Terminus of the Burning Abyss, so we are searching for Polymerization with Frightfur Patchwork which means that we can play both Guardian Chimera and potentially also make use of the Edge-Imp monsters. Your combo requires Red Resonator, Predaplant Ophrys Scorpio, Polymerization, and a monster to discard. But let’s say that instead of Poly and that monster discard, you have Frightfur Patchwork. Activate Patchwork to search for Poly and Edge-Imp Chain. Normal Summon Red Resonator and use it to Special Summon Scorpio from hand. Scorpio sends Chain to GY to Special Summon Predaplant Darlingtonia Cobra from Deck. Cobra Chain Link 1 and Chain Chain Link 2. Chain searches another Frightfur Patchwork and Cobra adds Ultra Polymerization. Ultra Poly fuses Cobra and Scorpio into Predaplant Ambulomelides. Ambulo adds Predapruning from Deck to hand on Fusion Summon. Banish Ultra Poly from GY to target Ambulo to Special Summon Cobra and Scorpio from GY. Link Cobra and Scorpio into Cherubini, Ebon Angel of the Burning Abyss. Cherubini sends Graff, Malebranche of the Burning Abyss from Deck to the GY to increase its own ATK. Graff triggers to Special Summon Cir, Malebranche of the Burning Abyss from Deck to Linkpoint. Activate Predapruning to get Scorpio from GY. Xyz Scorpio and Cir into Dante, Traveler of the Burning Abyss. Dante detaches Cir to mill any number of cards (does not really matter, but milling a Ritual Monster is good). Cir triggers to Special Summon Graff from GY to Linkpoint. Ambulo tributes itself to Special Summon another Scorpio from Deck. Synchro Red Resonator and Scorpio into Ib the World Chalice Justiciar who searches World Legacy Monstrosity on Synchro Summon. Activate Poly to fuse Cherubini, Dante Traveler of the Burning Abyss, and Graff into Dante, Pilgrim of the Burning Abyss. Now activate Monstrosity targeting it for 2 Level 9’s from Deck and you know the rest. This Deck is definitely something. You can’t get Bibliomuse from Deck when you target Fusion Dante with Monstrosity which is a definitely a big negative. There is no real benefit to playing this Deck other than having the ability to make Guardian Chimera for pops and draws on your following turn. But this does cross off Dante from my list of Level 9 monsters. 

For the Main Deck Monsters: 3 Prediction Princess Tarotrei, 1 Prediction Princess Tarotreith, and 3 Prediction Princess Bibliomuse. Tarotrei can Quick Effect flip a monster on field face-up or face-down and she can Special Summon a Flip Monster from hand or GY face-down during your End Phase. Tarotreith must either be Ritual Summoned or Special Summoned via Tarotrei's effect in the End Phase. Her Flip Effect Special Summons a Flip Monster from your Deck face-downn and she can also Quick Effect flip any number of your monsters face-up or face-down. Bibliomuse can Special Summon herself back face-down after being Tributed and sent there. Her Flip Effect adds a Prediction Princess monster other than herself and a Ritual Spell from Deck to hand and while she is face-up on the field, your Ritual Monsters gain targeting and destruction protection from your opponent’s card effects. 2 Deus-X Krawler which negates all activated monster effects on your opponent's side of the field after it has been flipped face-up and if it is destroyed on field, you can search for a Level 9 monster with a different Type and Attribute. 1 Pot of the Forbidden which has a Flip Effect that lets you choose between Drawing 2 cards, returning all Spell/Traps on the field to the hand, destroying all monsters your opponent controls, or looking at your opponent's hand and shuffling a card from it back into the Deck. 1 Mardel, Generaider Boss of Light which is a Level 9 target for Monstrosity in Deck and you can also easily get it onto the field with Lonefire Blossom and on Summon it either searches a Generaider card or a Plant monster. 1 Edge Imp Chain which adds a Frightfur card from Dec to hand if sent from hand or field to GY. 1 Edge Imp Sabres which can Special Summon itself from GY by placing a card from your hand on top of the Deck. 1 Graff, Malebranche of the Burning Abyss and 1 Cir, Malebranche of the Burning Abyss which we are only using for their GY effects. Graff Special Summons a BA from Deck if sent to GY and Cir targets and Special Summons a BA from GY except itself if sent to GY. 2 Lonefire Blossom which tributes a Plant to Special Summon a Plant from Deck. 3 Predaplant Ophrys Scorpio which sends a monster from hand to GY on Normal or Special Summon to Special Summon a Predaplant from Deck except itself. 1 Predaplant Darlingtonia Cobra which adds a Fusion or Polymerization Spell Card from Deck to hand if Special Summoned by the effect of a Predaplant monster once per Duel. And 3 Red Resonator which Special Summons a Level 4 or lower monster from hand on Normal Summon or targets a face-up monster on field to gain LP equal to that monster's ATK if Special Summoned.

For Spell/Traps: 3 Frightfur Patchwork which adds a Polymerization and an Edge Imp monster from Deck to hand. 2 Polymerization. 1 Ultra Polymerization which pays 2000 to Fusion Summon using 2 monsters you control where neither player can activate cards or effects in response to the activataion. And you can also banish it from GY and target a Fusion Monster Special Summoned by its effect to Special Summon the monsters used for its Summon from your GY with their effects negated and ATK/DEF reduced to 0. 1 Predapruning which Special Summons a Predaplant from GY and equips it with this card. 1 Underworld Ritual of Prediction which Ritual Summons a Prediction Princess Ritual Monster from hand or GY face-up or face-down and you can also banish it from GY to Special Summon a non-Ritual Prediction Princess from Deck face-down. 1 World Legacy Monstrosity which either Special Summons a Level 9 monster from hand or targets a Level 9 monster you control to Special Summon 2 Level 9 monsters from Deck with a different Type and Attribute than it but with different names. 3 Pot of Prosperity and 2 Resonator Call which you can optionally play at 3 if you wanted as it searches for a Resonator monster.

Extra Deck: 1 Trishula, the Dragon of Icy Imprisonment which is a monster you can optionally make instead of Dante in order to actually get Bibliomuse from Deck when using Monstrosity. 1 Guardian Chimera which you can also make for pops and draws and it is also a Level 9. 1 Dante, Pilgrim of the Burning Abyss. 1 Predaplant Ambulomelides which adds a Predap card from Deck to hand on Fusion Summon and can target and Tribute a monster to Special Summon a Predaplant monster from Deck. 1 Ib the World Chalice Justiciar which adds a World Legacy card from Deck to hand on Synchro Summon. 2 Herald of the Arc Light which adds a Ritual Monster or Ritual Spell from Deck to hand if sent to GY. 1 Mereologic Aggregator. 1 Laevateinn, Generaider Boss of Shadows and 1 Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity. 1 Dante, Traveller of the Burning Abyss which is a Rank 3 that detaches a material to send 1 to 3 cards from the top of your Deck to the GY to have himself gain 500 ATK for each card sent to the GY this way until the end of the turn. And if he is sent to GY, he can target a BA in GY and add it to your hand except himself. 1 Cherubini, Ebon Angel of the Burning Abyss which is a Link that needs 2 Level 3's as Link Material and it prevents monsters it points to from being destroyed by card effects and it can send a Level 3 from Deck to GY as cost to have a BA on field gain ATK/DEF equal to the sent monster's ATK/DEF until the end of the turn. 1 S:P Little Knight, 1 I:P Masquerena, and 1 Gravity Controller.

Side Deck: 2 Nibiru, the Primal Being, 3 Thunder King, the Lightningstrike Kaiju, 2 Gizmek Kaku, the Supreme Shining Sky Stag, 2 Dinowrestler Pankratops, 3 Dark Ruler No More, and 3 Evenly Matched.

deck_name: Coordius the Triphasic Dealmon Prediction Princess
deck_excerpt: The Next Greatest Innovation in Prediction Princess
deck_description:
The Level 9 monster that we are taking a look at today is Coordius the Triphasic Dealmon which is a Level 9 DARK Fiend Fusion Monster that needs a Synchro Monster, an Xyz Monster, and a Link Monster as Fusion Material. Once while this Fusion Summoned card is face-up on the field, you can pay LP in multiples of 2000 and choose to activate up to 3 effects based on every 2000 LP you paid. The first effect allows you to add a Spell/Trap from your GY to your hand. The second effect destroys exactly 3 cards your opponent controls. And the third effect has Coordius gain ATK equal to half the different between your LP and your opponent's LP for this turn only, but your other monsters cannot attack this turn. So, one way that you can Summon Coordius really easily is if you use Deep Sea Diva to Special Summon Neptabyss, the Atlantean Prince from Deck. Then, you would Synchro the two of them into Goyo Defender. Goyo Defender Special Summons 2 more copies of itself from Extra Deck. Xyz 2 of them into a Rank 3 and then Link that Xyz Monster and the remaining Goyo Defender into a Link-2 Monster. Now, if you have Miracle Synchro Fusion, you can go ahead and banish a Synchro, Xyz, and Link from field/GY to Fusion Summon Coordius. That works, but we are trying to play Prediction Princess here. We need a way to find World Legacy Monstrosity, Miracle Synchro Fusion, and have a Synchro, Xyz, and Link to Fuse into Coordius. And that is easily done utilizing the power of Red Resonator and Predaplant Ophrys Scorpio. And, we are also making use of some of the new Goblin Rider monsters from PHNI to get ourselves into the right position to get our materials for Coordius. Same 2.5-card combo: Red Resonator, Predaplant Ophrys Scorpio, and a monster to send for Scorpio's effect. Normal Red Resonator who Special Summons Scorpio. Scorpio sends a monster from hand to GY to Special Summon Predaplant Darlingtonia Cobra from Deck who searches for Miracle Synchro Fusion. Xyz Cobra and Scorpio into the new Goblin Rider Big-Head Gabonga who adds a Golin monster from Deck to hand on Xyz Summon. Add Goblin Rider Dug the Assaulter. Dug detaches a material from Gabonga to Special Summon itself from hand. Synchro Red Resonator and Dug into Ib the World Chalice Justiciar who adds World Legacy Monstrosity from Deck to hand on Synchro Summon. Link Gabonga and Ib into Donner, Dagger Fur Hire. Activate Miracle Synchro Fusion and banish Ib, Gabonga, and Donner from field/GY to Fusion Summon Coordius the Triphasic Dealmon from Extra Deck. Pay 2000 LP with Coordius to add back Miracle Synchro Fusion from GY. Activate Monstrosity targeting Coordius to get Prediction Princess Bibliomuse and Deus-X Krawler from Deck. Xyz Coordius and Deus-X into Mereologic Aggregator in the EMZ who sends Herald of the Arc Light from Extra Deck to GY. Herald triggers to add Prediction Princess Tarotrei from Deck to hand. Target Herald in GY with Aggregator and detach Deus-X to attach Herald from GY to itself. Link Aggregator into Gravity Controller. Herald hits the GY and triggers again to add Underworld Ritual of Prediction from Deck to hand. Activate Underworld Ritual to Ritual Summon Tarotrei by Tributing Bibliomuse. Bibliomuse Special Summons herself back from GY face-down. Tarotrei changes Bibliomuse to face-up Attack Position. Bibliomuse's Flip Effect triggers to add Prediction Princess Tarotreith and another Underworld Ritual from Deck to hand. Activate the Underworld Ritual you just searched to Ritual Summon Tarotreith face-down. Proceed to your End Phase and Tarotrei Special Summons Deus-X from GY face-down. During your opponent's Standby Phase, banish Underworld Ritual from GY as Chain Link 1 and activate Tarotrei's effect as Chain Link 2. Tarotrei changes Tarotreith to face-up Attack Position and Underworld Ritual Special Summons another Bibliomuse from Deck face-down. On a new Chain, Tarotreith's Flip Effect triggers to Special Summon Pot of the Forbidden from Deck face-down. Heading into your opponent's Main Phase, you can activate Tarotreith's effect to flip Bibliomuse, Deus-X, and Pot of the Forbidden face-up. Pot looks at your opponent's hand and shuffles a card from it back into the Deck, Deus-X negates all activated monster effects on your opponent's side of the field, and Bibliomuse searches for another Tarotrei and Underworld Ritual for next turn. That's a pretty good board you have. Now, let's look at what we can do on our next turn. We have the second Underworld Ritual in GY that we can use to get another Bibliomuse from Deck. We have the Tarotrei and Underworld Ritual in hand that we searched on our opponent's turn. And we have Miracle Synchro Fusion which is live and able to Fusion Summon another Coordius the Triphasic Dealmon from Extra Deck. Let's talk about that. We can banish Gravity Controller, Mereologic Aggregator, and Herald of the Arc Light from field/GY with Miracle Synchro Fusion to make another Coordius which is really good. So what can the second Coordius do? Well, if your opponent has 3 or more cards on their field, you can choose to pop 3 of them with Coordius and we can also add back the World Legacy Monstrosity in our GY which can target Coordius again to get 2 Level 9's from our Deck to go into Laevateinn, Generaider Boss of Shadows who Tributes itself to get Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity from our Extra Deck and suck up 2 to 3 cards from our opponnent's field depending on if we also Xyz using Coordius. We are never using that 3rd effect because the restriction on your other monsters not attacking is pretty bad if Coordius himself is not game. This is extremely good. I never would've thought that Coordius would be summonable in Prediction Princess and I never figured that it would be this good at setting up your board and setting up an incredible amount of follow-up for your following turn. If anything, I think that this replaces Ib Ham Prediction Princess. It functionally is Ib Ham Prediction Princess, but it has focus on making Coordius which just enables so much more than what Ib Ham Prediction Princess can do. This is functionally one of the best Prediction Princess builds that I have come across and experimented on and it is now my favorite build of Prediction Princess. 

For the Main Deck Monsters: 3 Prediction Princess Tarotrei, 1 Prediction Princess Tarotreith, and 3 Prediction Princess Bibliomuse. Tarotrei can Quick Effect flip a monster on field face-up or face-down and she can Special Summon a Flip Monster from hand or GY face-down during your End Phase. Tarotreith must either be Ritual Summoned or Special Summoned via Tarotrei's effect in the End Phase. Her Flip Effect Special Summons a Flip Monster from your Deck face-downn and she can also Quick Effect flip any number of your monsters face-up or face-down. Bibliomuse can Special Summon herself back face-down after being Tributed and sent there. Her Flip Effect adds a Prediction Princess monster other than herself and a Ritual Spell from Deck to hand and while she is face-up on the field, your Ritual Monsters gain targeting and destruction protection from your opponent’s card effects. 2 Deus-X Krawler which negates all activated monster effects on your opponent's side of the field after it has been flipped face-up and if it is destroyed on field, you can search for a Level 9 monster with a different Type and Attribute. 1 Pot of the Forbidden which has a Flip Effect that lets you choose between Drawing 2 cards, returning all Spell/Traps on the field to the hand, destroying all monsters your opponent controls, or looking at your opponent's hand and shuffling a card from it back into the Deck. 1 Mardel, Generaider Boss of Light which is a Level 9 target for Monstrosity in Deck and you can also easily get it onto the field with Lonefire Blossom and on Summon it either searches a Generaider card or a Plant monster. 3 Predaplant Ophrys Scorpio which sends a monster from your hand to the GY on Normal or Special Summon to Special Summon a Predaplant monster from your Deck other than itself. 1 Predaplant Darlingtonia Cobra which adds a Fusion or Polymerization Spell Card from Deck to hand if it is Special Summoned by the effect of a Predaplant Monster once per Duel. 2 Lonefire Blossom which Tributes a Plant monster to Special Summon a Plant monster from Deck. 1 Goblin Rider Dug the Assaulter which is a Level 3 monster we can Special Summon from hand by detaching an Xyz material from a monster on field. We aren't playing any Goblin Rider Spell/Traps, so it is not like we can make use of its other effect. But we just need it for the Summonable Level 3 body. It is not a hard brick since it can Summon itself from your hand, but you'd just prefer not to draw it. 3 Red Resonator which Special Summons a Level 4 or lower monster from hand on Normal Summon and targets a face-up monster on field on Special Summon to gain Life Points equal to that monster's ATK. 3 Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring. 

For Spell/Traps: 3 Pot of Prosperity. 3 Resonator Call which adds a Resonator monster from Deck to hand. 1 World Legacy Monstrosity which either Special Summons  Level 9 monster from your hand or targets a Level 9 monster you control to Special Summon 2 Level 9 monsters from your Deck with different Types and Attributes than that monster but with different names. 1 World Legacy Succession which Special Summons a monster from GY to Linkpoint. 1 Instant Fusion for Master of Ham. 1 Miracle Synchro Fusion which Fusion Summons a Fusion Monster that lits a Synchro Monster as material by banishing monsters from field and/or GY. 3 Underworld Ritual of Prediction which Ritual Summons a Prediction Princess Ritual Monster from hand or GY face-up or fac-edown and you can banish it from GY during the Standby Phase to Special Summon a non-Ritual Prediction Princess monster from Deck face-down. Finally, 3 Infinite Impermanence. 

Extra Deck: 1 Trishula, the Dragon of Icy Imprisonment. 2 Coordius the Triphasic Dealmon. 1 Master of Ham which Special Summons a Flip Monster from hand or Deck face-down on Fusion Summon. 1 Ib the World Chalice Justiciar which adds a World Legacy card from Deck to hand on Synchro Summon. 2 Herald of the Arc Light which adds a Ritual Monster or Ritual Spell from Deck to hand if sent to GY. 1 Merelogic Aggregator. 1 Laevateinn, Generaider Boss of Shadows and 1 Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity. 1 Goblin Rider Big-Head Gabonga which is a Rank 3 Xyz that searches a Goblin monster from Deck on Xyz Summon. That's all that we are using it for, but it can attach a face-up monster on field to itself if a material(s) is detached from a monster(s) on field which can be used as removal perhaps. 1 Donner, Dagger Fur Hire which is a Link-2 that needs 2 monsters with different Types and can target a Fur Hire you control and a mosnter your opponent controls to destroy them. This just gives Donner some added usage other than being a Link Monster we are banishing with Miracle Synchro Fusion to make Coordius, but you can realistically use any Link-2 you want. Even Baba Barber if you really wanted. 1 S:P Little Knight, 1 I:P Masquerena, and 1 Gravity Controller.

Side Deck: 3 Nibiru, the Primal Being, 3 Thunder King, the Lightningstrike Kaiju, 2 Gizmek Kaku, the Supreme Shining Sky Stag, 2 Lightning Storm, 2 Dark Ruler No More, and 3 Evenly Matched.

deck_excerpt: Black-Winged Assault Dragon FTK ft. Beelze + Cupid
deck_description:
Danger in the soaring skies! A diabolic dragon is willing to assault your opponent with an angel. Interesting, huh?

 

 

Gameplan

1) Plant a flower to opposing side with "Black Garden". Then, Synchro Summon Assault Dragon by using Accel + Formula as materials.

2) Synchro Summon Cupid by using Shamisen + Exodia/Idol as materials and reduce the level of Cupid by 3.

3) Special Summon Shamisen with its ability by shuffling Formula back into Extra Deck. Then, Synchro Summon Beelze by using Librarian + Shamisen as materials and pass Beelze to opponent by destroying the flower while replacing it with "Mystic Box".

4) Synchro Summon Formula by using Exodia/Idol + Cupid as materials.

5) What is going to happen is as follows:

  1. Cupid deals damage.
  2. Beelze gains ATK, which is mandatory and not hard once per turn.
  3. Assault Dragon deals damage because opponent activated monster effect, which is Beelze. Assault Dragon's effect isn't also hard once per turn.
  4. First, action in #2 happens. Then, #3 happens. It's mandatory endless loop, until someone dies.

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contact Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Black-Winged Assault Dragon" can be collected by purchasing "Blackwing's Pride" deck. 30 UR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Into The Void" + "Allure of Darkness" can be found within "The Infinite Void" Secret Pack to save 180 SR!

- "Formula Synchron" can be found within "Stardust Ties" Secret Pack to save 90 SR!

- "Black Garden" can be found within "Exquisite Jet-Black Rose" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "T.G. Hyper Librarian" can be found within "Futuristic Creatures" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Moray of Avarice" can be found within "Treasures of the Cosmic Ocean" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Wonder Wand" and "Spellbook of Knowledge" can be collected by purchasing "Spellbook of Prophecy" deck. 120 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 540 SR and 90 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. Let me know if you have any questions and have fun in Master Duel!

deck_name: Sentinel Black Flame - Masha (Yu-Gi-Oh! GX Tag Force)
deck_description: Masha uses Decks that aim to lock down the opponent's Spell and Trap Cards with "Horus the Black Flame Dragon".

With this Deck we aim to create a strong and resilient Board turn 1 to outressource our Opponent through the Grind game which the Earthbounds and Runicks offer us by abusing the effect of Harmonic Synchrofusion.

Why should I play this Deck?:
Runick/Earthbound has many advantages which include:
1. Being able to synchro into nearly every level due to how the Earthbound and Runick engine interacts (basicaly everything from 3-12 is possible)
2. The Deck has a great grindgame and rewards good deckbuilding and plays due to how Synchrofusion and the Runick extra Deck Monsters work
3. The Deck offers a great grindgame
4. The Earthbound and Runick Cores are quite small, leaving us with 9 Flex Spots for Handtraps, extenders, Powerspells etc.
5. Due to Groundskeeper, Hugin and Slumber our Fireking Matchup is quite good
6. Great Fusion/Synchro acces 

What are the dissadvantages of this Deck?
1. In the current Format a lot of the Handtraps like Droll etc. can kill our Deck very easily. Depending on our Hand, even Nibiru can become a huge Problem
2. Our Monsters are light/dark which enables opponents Bystials
3. If our Groundkeeper gets negated or we are Drolled when activating sweeper, our Endboard quickly turns into Runick+Handtraps
4. The extra Deck can get quiet expensive with cards like Chaosangel, Sleipnir etc.
The most basic combo this Deck has is: Stone Sweeper/Groundskeeper+1 Runick Spell


Given the power that this first turn offers, I believe that the Deck has a lot of potential and if you have read up until here you are probably at least interested in how this Deck works. For this reason you see a Combo Guide for the most basic combo of this Deck down below

Discard Sweeper to add Groundskeeper-> Summon Groundskeeper and use his effect to summon Linewalker out of the Deck-> Linewalkers effect triggers to add Harmonic Synchrofusion to your hand-> Use your Runick Spell to Summon Hugin-> activate Harmonic Synchrofusion sending Linewalker and Hugin to summon Dragostapelia and Denglong-> Denglong effect to add 1 Nine Pillars of the Yang Zing to hand
-If you have another runick spell or drew into it via Fountain you can also summon Sleipnir and go for a synchro 10 play for either Chengying, Chaosangel or Baronne de Fleur by using Sleipnir+Groundskeeper
Endboard: Denglong+Nine Pillars, Dragostapelia, Synchro 10 and 2 cards in Hand


I hope you enjoyed this deckbreakdown and if you did I would be happy to hear your suggestions, especially for the extra Deck slots :)

This deck got a very good field spell now, in fact it's a combo by itself! 

Here's a combo:

Activate nightmare throne

Add lotus

normal lotus

tribute it and summon spirit from your deck.

add nightmare pain.

actuvate nightmare pain

Use nightmare pain's effect to destroy spirit and add grave squirmer.

Spirit effect summon Yubel throne effect add and summon terror incarnate.

activate squirmer and summon it by destroying yubel

Use yubel to summon incarnate.

link incarnate and squirmer for ip 

Use incarnate's effect to summon nightmare from the deck.

link ip, incarnate, and nightmare for apollosa

Use incarnate to summon nightmare from the grave

Use your squirmer to revive a monster and make sp little knight.

yeah it's dumb but apparently yubel can do that now, so lol.

This combo essentially drops all of you dead cards (basically monsters that are only able to be summoned by yubel, you're freely able to summon them from the graveyard with the same effects that dumps them from the deck, so those monsters are best off out of your deck as they will be a dead draw in the future) from your deck and sets up 4 interruptions. There's probably more stuff you can do with this general concept but I think you get the general idea.

deck_excerpt: Raye (and her friends Roze, Little Knight, TY-Phon and Zeus) are ready to tackle the January 2024 TCG meta!
deck_description:
Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!

Who is gonna win? An entire army of monsters, or a single girl in a mech suit?

My money is on Raye (and her friends Roze, Little Knight, TY-Phon and Zeus), since she is more powerful than ever with not one, BUT TWO COPIES OF ENGAGE, ONE OF THE MOST BUSTED CARD IN YUGIOH!

New cards in the Striker arsenal include Triple Tactics Thrust, which is essentially another copy of Engage or any other blind second boardbreaker you have. This incredible spell card is almost always live, since opponents generally play on your turn with their own deck's monster effects (for example, Fire Kings).Thrust is kind of more affordable now with the recent reprint as well!

The Extra deck notably has TY-Phon, since you can turn a stolen monster (of course in addition to your MANY ways of taking a monster, you can now steal with triple Mind Control) into a beefy beatstick floodgate! Your enemy's XYZ monster and the ever common TY-Phon can be stolen and turn into Zeus in main phase 2 as well! Little Knight and Azalea offer additional removal on the field.

A cool interaction with Linkage is that it can turn your Little Knight, TY-Phon or Zeus into a Sky Striker Ace and you can go back to your Striker gameplan!

The philosophy with Blind Second Sky Strikers is to wipe out most if not all of your opponent's resources that they slap down on the board going first, and then close out the match with Sky Striker's unparalleled grind game.

This deck has cards specifically picked out for the January 2024 meta, like Triple Tactics Talents/Thrust (super good since duelists often monster effects during your turn or handtraps you) and 9 monster stealing cards (particularly good at cracking Fire King boards).

The current meta allows for Evenly Matched and Raigeki to obliterate most duelist's boards this format since they spend all their resources building their "unbreakable" board only to fall to 1-2 cards - allowing your Sky Striker gameplan to go off unhindered and out-resource your opponent.

When your opponent forces you to go 1st thinking all you do is spam "Raigeki" and "Evenly Matched," metagame them by siding in all your handtraps in the sidedeck, as well as your searchable normal trap floodgates like Dimensional Barrier and Different Dimensional Ground!

If your weakened opponent hasn't surrendered yet due to the sheer resource advantage and offensive pressure this deck generates, you can clear the board with a plethora of cards including Linkage, allowing Raye to OTK all by herself!

If you have any questions about this deck, feel free to ask me in the comments below!

GLHF Duelists!

Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!

The 2024 Dino Deck for Master Duel
Itterally just a fun deck I made. Was running arround Master Duel with sometihng simular for a bit, did pretty ok wih it.

(Disclaimer: If your opponent is smart, they don't activate Maxx "C" and you lose no matter what. This is the only issue you need to be concerned of.)

Have you ever wondered how to mill your opponent with Maxx "C" on the very first turn itself? Although not a guaranteed FTK, if your opponent is happy-go-lucky, consider yourself really lucky.

 

 

Gameplan

1) Check these options before/during the game and change them as shown, which matters later on:

  • Self-Chain >>> On
  • Card Position >>> Manual
  • Activation Order Settings >>> On

2) At one point, play these cards or combos at any time but End Phase...

  • Activate "Gift Exchange" and choose Maxx "C" as the target. I hope your opponent activates it, which is all that matters.
  • Activate "Temple >>> Rebirth" combo and choose Types of monsters in GYs as Zombie, which synergizes well with Hela. Then, destroy Temple + Rebirth with "Twin Twisters" by discarding Samsara. If you can't discard Samsara with "Twin Twisters", you can also do that with Dugares.
  • Activate "Double Summon", which will be used for Wanghu. When Ravenous is present, Special Summon Hela with Saryuja and Normal Summon Wanghu. Then, pass Wanghu to your opponent with "Shien's Spy" but if your oppponent's side is full, feel free to play "Raigeki" and clear their side.

3) There is nothing else to do right now. So, if you have "Wattfox" in-hand and "Into the Void" was played beforehand, jump into End Phase but not before changing the button at the lower right corner of the screen to "ON" to not miss anything...

  1. Change "Card Position" from "Manual" to "Auto" because there will be lots of Special Summoning and you don't want to waste any time with manual labor.
  2. Start giving your opponent Maxx "C" by triggering "Gift Exchange".
  3. Activate Samsara to Special Summon. To your opponent's knowledge, Wanghu can destroy Samsara but Maxx "C" can also draw a card, if this interaction happens. Pray your opponent takes the bait and if they do, proceed with next step. Otherwise, repeat Special Summoning Samsara until your opponent activates Maxx "C".
  4. After the activation of Maxx "C", chain into Ravenous and discard Wattfox + Any and target anything but Hela/Wanghu. Then, make a follow-up with Hela by tributing Hela and targeting Wattfox in GY to Special Summon it. Even though Wattfox isn't Zombie by default, "Rebirth Judgment" changed the outcome in that regard, so that Hela can be able to pick Wattfox.
  5. With Chain Link 4 ended, everything has been done in order. So, Wanghu will destroy Samsara and Wattfox. Samsara isn't important but Wanghu destroying Wattfox is a huge deal. Your opponent can't be able to activate anything to stop this Mill combo now.
  6. Since your opponent can't activate anything, that includes Wanghu destroying Samsara. Kindly return Wanghu to where it belongs by pressing the button of "Shien's Spy".
  7. Finally, you can Special Summon Samsara and Wanghu can destroy it. Meanwhile, your opponent draws one by one. Repeat this process until your opponent is completely deck-out to seal your victory.

(Disclaimer: There is a chance you can hit "Morphing Jar #2" instead of "Jackpot 7". If it happens, you lose.)

Greetings! In this deck, we are trying to hit the jackpot with "Morphing Jar #2". Although not guaranteed to win, it's worth giving a shot.

 

Gameplan

1) When you have 4 cards in your Main Deck, Link Summon Saryuja and activate it. There, you draw all remaining cards and shuffle back three, which has to be "Jackpot 7".

2) Destroy everything with "Dark Hole" because you don't want to shuffle any Main Deck monsters with "Morphing Jar #2". When you have "Morphing Jar #2" in your hand and if you have played "Into the Void" beforehand, set All-Out Attacks + 2 x Reverse Reuse + Offerings to the Doomed and end your turn. Also, set the button at the lower right corner of the screen to "ON" and don't miss anything happening.

3) During your opponent's Draw Phase, activate first "Reverse Reuse" and target "Morphing Jar #2" to Special Summon it to opposing side as face-down. Then, follow-up with "All-Out Attacks" to make "Morphing Jar #2" face-up. If you are lucky, "Morphing Jar #2" mills all three "Jackpot 7" cards. Since it has been considered as effect done by your opponent, even if you originally own "Morphing Jar #2", you win the duel anyways...

  • However, as mentioned previously, it all comes down to whether you are lucky or not. If you couldn't hit all three "Jackpot 7" cards, you can give another and final attempt. When "Morphing Jar #2" is at your side as face-up, chain into "Offerings to the Doomed" and destroy "Morphing Jar #2". Reason is that milling effect coming from "Morphing Jar #2" has to be done by your opponent, not you. So, when "Morphing Jar #2" is in your GY, activate second "Reverse Reuse", just like how you did back then. I hope you win this time.

deck_description:
So, "Jackpot 7" decks are well-known if went as second, with "Dark Scorpion Burglars" in mind. However, you can also go first with "Dark Scorpion Burglars" thanks to turn skip coming from Arcana. Alongside Panda package, it's more consistent than ever.

 

 

Gameplan

1) When you have Link Summoned Saryuja and "Light Barrier" is present, Special Summon Arcana with Saryuja. Choose the outcome as heads to always skip your opponent's turn at the cost of sending two of your monsters to GY.

2) If you haven't already, shuffle back "Jackpot 7" cards with their abilities. Then, if you have played "Into the Void" while holding "Dark Scorpion Burglars", set Give and Take + Tri-Wight and end your turn. Send any two monsters to GY with Arcana and make sure you have at least 3 x Main Monster Zones (MMZ) free, which will be reserved for Tri-Wight.

3) When it's your turn, activate "Give and Take" and target on "Dark Scorpion Burglars" to Special Summon it to opposing side. Then, play "Tri-Wight" to bring forth 3 x Level 1 dudes. Next, tackle into Burglars with Level 1 dudes. Since you took Battle Damage, you can send all three "Jackpot 7" cards to GY because they were sent by your opponent's card effect, namely Burglars.

4) Congratulations, you win the duel!
