really OP deck profile!
OP Floo deck build

Subterror is a Flip Monster archetype just like Prediction Princess and they even have their own Level 9 monster in Subterror Behemoth Voltelluric. Voltelluric is a Level 9 EARTH Thunder Flip Monster that has a Flip Effect that allos you to target a set monster your opponent controls and take control of it until your next End Phase. And, it shares the Subeterror Behemoth monster effect of being able to Special Summon itself from hand in Defense Position when a face-up monster you control is flipped face-down and you control no face-up monsters after that. And its last effect is a soft once per turn effect that allows you to change it to face-down Defense Position. I haven't played Subterror before, neither Guru Control nor the Subterror Behemoth version. I am not too sure about how to play Subterror alone as a Deck, but I am pretty sure that Voltelluric is definitely one of the Behemoths that you at the very most play just the 1-of in the Behemoth version. I don't really see it as being that good of a card, nor are we actually going to be using its Flip Effect in this Subterror Prediction Princess Deck. From what I can see, the Subterror monsters mainly just work for their own archetype. They are not like the Shaddolls or the Krawlers who have Flip Effects that are more general in what they do. The Subterror Flip Effects more-so help their own gameplan, but some actually have some pretty generically good effects that we can make use of. Subterror Behemoth Umastryx has a Flip Effect that allows you to target a monster your opponent controls and banish it. Subterror Behemoth Ultramafus has a Flip Effect that allows you to change all other face-up monsters on the field to face-down Defense Position. In a more generalized Prediction Princess Deck that is playing Umastryx and Ultramafus as Flip Monster options, I would see these being very useful. But for my ideology in what Prediction Princess should be and in this Deck in particular, they are not very good. Umastryx, while it is not bad at all, just is going to be another monster on your field. And considering that your Prediction Princess combo is filling up almost, if not, your entire field, I would much rather not play it in favor of monsters with better Flip Effects like Deus-X Krawler or Subterror Guru (for this Deck) or monsters with additional benefits like Prediction Princess Bibliomuse giving your Ritual Monsters targeting and destruction protection in addition to it searching a non-Ritual Prediction Princess and a Ritual Spell for follow-up. As for Ultramafus, being a walking Book of Eclipse is pretty good, but considering how it also affects your field, I would much rather not play it. Sure, it can reset Bibliomuse and Prediction Princess Tarotreith's Flip Effects, but at the same time, it stops Deus-X Krawler's continuous effect since it is no longer face-up on the field. And sure, you could just instead go for Whirlwind Weasel and Guard Dog whose Flip Effects linger throughout the rest of the turn after they've been flipped up and triggered, but as the Level/Rank 9 bozo that I am, I would much rather play Deus-X. Also, with how we are just shotgunning all of our Flip Effects in the Standby Phase, you aren't really going to get a chance to use Ultramafus as interruption anyways. Going back to Voltelluric, because it is an EARTH monster, we can't get Bibliomuse out of the Deck for access to it if we target Voltelluric with Monstrosity. So we have to be a little creative. We are going to be using the Predaplant engine with Scorpio and Cobra to get ourselves Instant Fusion from Deck. We are not playing Red Resonator because if we are going to make this Deck 40 cards, we can't really fit 3 Red Resonator and 3 Resonator Call. But that just means that we have to hard draw World Legacy Monstrosity which is definitely an option, but we can still go without it if we don't draw it. We are also going to be making use of Trishula, the Dragon of Icy Imprisonment in our combo which is going to be a way for us to get another Level 9 on the field to go for a Rank 9. The cards we need for our combo are Predaplant Ophrys Scorpio, The Hidden City, and a monster to send to GY for Scorpio. Normal Scorpio and send a monster from hand to GY to Special Summon Predaplant Darlingtonia Cobra from Deck. Cobra searches us Instant Fusion from Deck. Activate The Hidden City and grab ourselves a copy of Subterror Fiendess. Activate Instant Fusion to get Master of Ham from our Extra Deck. Master of Ham triggers on Fusion Summon to Special Summon Subterror Behemoth Voltelluric from Deck face-down. We are not getting Bibliomuse because we are trying to work with Voltelluric and this is the only way that I can conceivably see us getting Voltelluric onto the field easily. We can't really use its own effect to Summon itself and we can't really use Subterror Nemesis Warrior either because we would need it and at least 1 other monster on field whose combined Levels are 9 or more to Tribute to get Voltelluric. We can't really get another monster on field for that exactly and we still wouldn't be getting to Bibliomuse or a Rank 9 either because that is if we have Instant Fusion and Nemesis Warrior already on field and we would also still need to be able to make Fusion Trish. Either way, we would then use The Hidden City to flip up Voltelluric. Then we banish Master of Ham, Ophrys Scorpio, and Darlingtonia Cobra to Special Summon Trishula from Extra Deck. Now here is where we can do a couple of things. If we don't have Monstrosity, we can overlay Voltelluric and Trish into Mereologic Aggregator to send Herald of the Arc Light to search and reattach and Link off and stuff and if we have Bibliomuse in hand or a Tarotrei or Tarotreith already in hand, we have full Prediction Princess combo. If we have Monstrosity, we can activate it targeting Trish to get Bibliomuse and Gizmek Kaku, the Supreme Shining Sky Stag from Deck. We then overlay Trish and Kaku into Aggregator, send Herald, reattach, Link off for searches... blah blah. But in this situation, we have Voltelluric on field and Fiendess in hand. If our opponent tries to interrupt Monstrosity, we can Fiendess to negate since we have a face-up Subterror on field. The same goes for if they try to negate Aggregator or Herald since Voltelluric is still on field. But if we don't need to negate, we can use Voltelluric and Aggregator to Link into I:P Masquerena. Ritual Summon by Tributing Bibliomuse for full Prediction Princess combo and use Tarotrei to Special Summon back Voltelluric from GY during the End Phase who will be flipped face-up by Tarotreith next turn to turn on Fiendess for a negate. With what we are working with, this version of Subterror Prediction Princess definitely isn't too bad. To a degree, we are making use of Voltelluric and having access to an omni negate with Fiendess is also really nice. This isn't the greatest Prediction Princess list that I have worked with, but it definitely is pretty unique in what it can do (I haven't explained Guru yet). The main issue here is that we can't search for Monstrosity and we cannot always access Bibliomuse as that requires we have Monstrosity. Definitely not bad, but definitely not the best.

For the Main Deck monsters: 3 Prediction Princess Tarotrei, 1 Prediction Princess Tarotreith, and 3 Prediction Princess Bibliomuse. Tarotrei can Quick Effect flip a monster on field face-up or face-down and during your End Phase, she can Special Summon a Flip Monster from hand or GY face-down. Tarotreith must either be Ritual Summoned or Special Summoned via Tarotrei’s End Phase effect. Her Flip Effect Special Summons a Flip Monster from your Deck face-down and she can also Quick Effect flip any number of your monsters face-up or face-down. Bibliomuse can Special Summon herself back from the GY face-down if she is Tributed and sent there. Her Flip Effect adds a Prediction Princess monster other than herself and a Ritual Spell from your Deck to your hand and while she is face-up on the field, your Ritual Monsters gain targeting and destruction protection from your opponent’s effects. 1 Deus-X Krawler which negates all activated monster effects on your opponent’s side of the field after it has been flipped face-up and if it is destroyed on field, you can search for a Level 9 monster with a different Type and Attribute than it. 2 Gizmek Kaku, the Supreme Shining Sky Stag and 1 Mardel, Generaider Boss of Light. Kaku is a Level 9 target for Monstrosity to Summon from Deck if we target Voltelluric and it is an easily Summonable Level 9 in general. Mardel is another Level 9 in the Deck to Summon off of Monstrosity if we are targeting Voltelluric and we can also get it off of Lonefire Blossom also. On Summon it adds a Generaider card or a Plant monster from Deck to hand. 1 Subterror Behemoth Voltelluric. 1 Subterror Guru. This card is actually not bad. If I wasn't focusing on utilizing Voltelluric, I’d be just playing Guru, Fiendess, Subterror Final Battles, and Hidden City as the only Subterror cards in the Deck because they alone are just that good. If I were to describe an actually good version of Subterror Prediction Princess, it’d just be Guru Control with Prediction Princess and without any floodgates (other than Deus-X maybe). Guru’s Flip Effect adds a Subterror card from Deck to hand other than itself. And while it is face-up on the field, it can target another face-up monster on the field and change both itself and that monster to face-down Defense Position. This effect is a Quick Effect if you control another Subterror card. If anything, we are just playing the 1 copy of Guru as a possible Flip Monster to Special Summon from Deck, or hand if we searched for it off of the activation of Hidden City instead of Fiendess. If we could fit more monsters on our side of the field I’d definitely play 2 copies to have a better chance of getting to this card or for having more incentive to actually Summon it. You could Special Summon Guru from Deck off of Tarotreith instead of Deus-X which gives you the ability to use both of its effects for interruption. On Flip, you add Fiendess for an omni-negate and since you control another Subterror in Voltelluric, you can Quick Effect book an opponent’s monster as well. But I feel like Deus-X is just better in what it can do, but that doesn’t mean Guru is particularly bad or anything. If anything, it is really good and very interesting, but an omni and a book don’t compare to negating all activated monster effects on your opponent’s side of the field. 2 Subterror Fiendess. When your opponent activates a card or effect you can Quick Effect send it from hand or field to GY to target a Subterror monster you control and negate the activation, changing the targeted Subterror to face-down Defense. And you can target a face-up monster you control to change it to face-down Defense Position to Special Summon a Subterror monster from hand or GY in face-up or face-down Defense Position. I guess that this is another way to get Voltelluric onto the field, but at the same time, it proves to have the same issues with if we were to try to get Voltelluric onto the field, if not even more issues. You can’t get Bibliomuse from Deck if you target Voltelluric with Monstrosity, you have to actually draw Fiendess and Voltelluric or find a way to get Voltelluric from Deck into the GY, and you actually have to hard-draw Monstrosity. I would much rather be using Fiendess for the omni-negate than using it for its other effect. Perhaps it can come up in situations revolving around you Special Summoning Guru and getting an additional copy of Fiendess for your following turn, but I don’t see it being used too often in this Deck. 3 Predaplant Ophrys Scorpio, 1 Predaplant Darlingtonia Cobra, and 2 Lonefire Blossom. I cannot express how good Master of Ham is. And with it being a Level 5 Fusion Monster who is able to be Summoned off of Instant Fusion, it practically means that you should be doing almost everything you can to get to Instant Fusion. And the fact that Scorpio and Cobra accomplish that while also giving you 2 additional bodies on field is just so incredible that it has resulted in me including them in a lot of versions of Prediction Princess. Scorpio sends a monster from hand to GY on Normal or Special Summon to Special Summon a Predaplant monster from Deck except for itself. Cobra searches for a Fusion or Polymerization Spell Card upon being Special Summoned by the effect of a Predaplant monster once per Duel. And Lonefire Blossom tributes a Plant monster as a soft once per turn to Special Summon a Plant monster from Deck.

Spell/Traps: 1 Instant Fusion for Master of Ham. 3 Underworld Ritual of Prediction which Ritual Summons a Prediction Princess Ritual Monster from hand or GY face-up or face-down and you can banish it from GY during the Standby Phase to Special Summon a non-Ritual Prediction Princess from Deck face-down. 2 Prediction Ritual which specifically Ritual Summons Prediction Princess Tarotrei and you can banish it from GY except during the turn it was sent there in order to search for a Prediction Princess monster. 3 Pre-Preparation of Rites. 3 Pot of Prosperity. 1 Terraforming. 3 The Hidden City. On activation, it adds a Subterror monster from Deck to hand and once per turn, it can change a face-down Defense Position Subterror monster you control to face-up Attack or Defense Position. Those are the 2 effects we are mainly using but Hidden City has a 3rd effect which once per turn allows you to change a face-down Subterror monster you control to face-up Attack or Defense Position when an opponent’s monster declares an attack to negate that attack. And 3 World Legacy Monstrosity which either Special Summons a Level 9 monster from hand or targets a Level 9 monster you control to Special Summon 2 Level 9 monsters from your Deck with a different Type and Attribute but with different names.

Extra Deck: 1 Trishula, the Dragon of Icy Imprisonment which can be Special Summoned from the Extra Deck by banishing 3 monsters you control with different names. 1 Master of Ham which Special Summons a Flip Monster from hand or Deck on Fusion Summon. 2 Herald of the Arc Light which adds a Ritual Monster or a Ritual Spell from Deck to hand if sent to GY. 1 Divine Arsenal AA-Zeus - Sky Thunder. 1 Infinitrack Earth Slicer. 2 Mereologic Aggregator. 1 Laevateinn, Generaider Boss of Shadows and 1 Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity. 1 Apollousa, Bow of the Goddess, 1 Cross-Sheep, 1 S:P Little Knight, 1 I:P Masquerena, and 1 Gravity Controller.

Side Deck: 2 Nibiru, the Primal Being, 3 Thunder King, the Lightningstrike Kaiju, 3 Dark Ruler No More, 1 Harpie’s Feather Duster, 2 Lightning Storm. 3 Evenly Matched, and 1 Subterror Final Battle (as an option).

deck_excerpt: The absolute travesty that is Overmind Archfiend
deck_description:
I enjoyed Sayer as a character in 5D’s and I enjoyed playing 3-axis Psychic Synchro when I still played Duel Links like 4 years ago. But I have to admit that Overmind Archfiend is one of the cards with the worst material requirements that I have ever experimented with. Overmind Archfiend is the Level 9 monster that we are looking at today. It is a Level 9 DARK Psychic Synchro Monster that requires a Psychic Tuner monster and 2 or more non-Tuner Psychic monsters as Synchro Material. As a soft once per turn, it can banish a Psychic monster from your GY. And when it leaves the field, it Summons as many of the monsters that were banished by its effect. And this effect to Summon does not miss timing because it is mandatory. Usually I would have no issue with Synchro Monsters that require 2 or more non-Tuners as material like Trishula, Dragon of the Ice Barrier or Mist Wurm because they are fairly generic and actually have pretty good effects that you can use. And then you have the ones that aren’t generic like Archfiend Zombie Skull, Chaos Goddess, and the Nordic Gods. But they have cards that actually help you to Summon them like Pain Painter for Archfiend Zombie Skull, Chaos Witch for Chaos Goddess, and the numerous ways that you can immediately cheat out the Nordic Gods or the many different ways you can put out a bunch of monsters to Synchro Summon them. Overmind Archfiend has none of these things. It was released in Crossroads of Chaos which debuted Psychic monsters like Silent Psychic Wizard, Serene Psychic Witch, Hushed Psychic Cleric, Psi-Beast, Mental Seeker, and Esper Girl. I think that these cards were supposed to work with Psychic Feel Zone which was also released in the same set and they do banish Psychic monsters to set up Feel Zone, so you could use it to possibly cheat out Overmind Archfiend, but we have no use for an unsearchable card in Psychic Feel Zone. Now, Overmind Archfiend’s effect isn’t terrible. In fact, if you have an Overmind Archfiend on field and a properly summoned Overmind Archfiend in GY, you can have the one on field banish the one in GY which will then Summon it back after it leaves the field and since it is a soft once per turn on its effect, you can keep looping the 2 Overmind Archfiends over and over. In a world where I would be able to consistently Synchro Summon 2 Overmind Archfiends turn 1, I would definitely be doing this. But we live in a godless world where that god was replaced with the infernal hive mind that told Konami that it was a good idea to give Overmind Archfiend the worst Synchro Material requirements in existence. Just like how Thought Ruler Archfiend was Sayer’s ace monster, we need to play the neo-Sayer cards to be able to summon Overmind Archfiend with the help of the P.U.N.K. monsters. Noh-P.U.N.K. Ze Amin is our Psychic-Type Tuner of choice and we can search for Psychic Tracker with P.U.N.K. JAM Dragon Drive which is a free Summon from hand as Psychic non-Tuner after Noh-P.U.N.K. Deer Note Special Summons Ze Amin back from GY. We need the help of Overdrive Teleporter to get us to Ze Amin to start our P.U.N.K. combo and get our second Level 3 non-Tuner Psychic to make Overmind Archfiend. 

The deal with Overdrive Teleporter is that it cannot be Special Summoned, so we need to Tribute Summon it. We could play Brain Research Lab for an extra Normal Summon of a Psychic monster, but Emergency Teleport is at 3 and we are playing Instant Fusion in this Deck for Master of Ham already. Our goal is to get to Mereologic Aggregator and all you need for that is Normal Summoning Overdrive Teleporter. But let’s say that we want Bibliomuse access as well, so let’s throw in World Legacy Monstrosity into the mix. That makes our starting combo consist of Emergency Teleport, Overdrive Teleporter, World Legacy Monstrosity, and an additional card in hand to send to GY for Foxy Tune. Again, we don’t necessarily Monstrosity for our combo, but if we want Bibliomuse, we do need it. E-Tele for Ze Amin from Deck. Tribute Ze Amin for Overdrive Teleporter. Pay 2000 to Special Summon Ze Amin and Psychic Tracker from Deck. Ze Amin pay 600 LP to add Noh-P.U.N.K. Foxy Tune from Deck. Activate Foxy Tune in hand and send a card in hand to GY to Special Summon Noh-P.U.N.K. Deer Note from Deck. Synchro Ze Amin and Deer Note into P.U.N.K. JAM Dragon Drive. Chain Link 1 JAM Dragon Drive, Chain Link 2 Deer Note in GY, Chain Link 3 Ze Amin in GY. Ze Amin boosts Dragon Drive, Deer Note Special Summons Ze Amin from GY, and Jam Dragon Drive adds another Psychic Tracker from Deck to hand. Special Summon Tracker from hand and Synchro Ze Amin and your 2 Psychic Trackers into Overmind Archfiend. Overmind banishes Ze Amin from GY. Link Overmind Archfiend and JAM Dragon Drive into I:P Masquerena. Overmind mandatory triggers upon being sent to GY to Special Summon the Ze Amin you banished. Synchro Ze Amin and Overdrive Teleporter into Cloudcastle. Cloudcastle on Synchro Summon Special Summons Overmind Archfiend back from GY. Now, if you didn’t have Monstrosity, you would just Xyz the two of them into Aggregator, but we are going with if we had Monstrosity in this instance here. Monstrosity target Overmind to get Prediction Princess Bibliomuse and Deus-X Krawler from Deck. Xyz Deus-X and Cloudcastle into Aggregator who sends Herald of the Arc Light from Extra Deck to GY to search for Prediction Princess Tarotrei, reattach Herald from GY, and Link Aggregator and Overmind Archfiend into Sky Striker Ace - Camellia. Herald triggers again to add Underworld Ritual of Prediction. And the rest is just the same Prediction Princess combo. Is this good? Not in the slightest. There are plenty of other Prediction Princess variants that I have combed through that can either do much more in a much easier fashion or they simply are able to access the whole Prediction Princess combo with much easier consistency and success. Like I didn’t even need to visit Li Shuwen since I am already bleeding from all orifices from building this Deck.

For the Main Deck Monsters: 3 Prediction Princess Tarotrei, 1 Prediction Princess Tarotreith, and 3 Prediction Princess Bibliomuse. Tarotrei can Quick Effect flip a monster on field face-up or face-down and she can Special Summon a Flip Monster from hand or GY face-down during your End Phase. Tarotreith must either be Ritual Summoned or Special Summoned via Tarotrei's effect in the End Phase. Her Flip Effect Special Summons a Flip Monster from your Deck face-downn and she can also Quick Effect flip any number of your monsters face-up or face-down. Bibliomuse can Special Summon herself back face-down after being Tributed and sent there. Her Flip Effect adds a Prediction Princess monster other than herself and a Ritual Spell from Deck to hand and while she is face-up on the field, your Ritual Monsters gain targeting and destruction protection from your opponent’s card effects. 1 Deus-X Krawler which negates all activated monster effects on your opponent's side of the field after it has been flipped face-up and if it is destroyed on field, you can search for a Level 9 monster with a different Type and Attribute. 1 Pot of the Forbidden which has a Flip Effect that lets you choose between Drawing 2 cards, returning all Spell/Traps on the field to the hand, destroying all monsters your opponent controls, or looking at your opponent's hand and shuffling a card from it back into the Deck. For the P.U.N.K. monsters: 2 Noh-P.U.N.K. Foxy Tune, 2 Noh-P.U.N.K. Deer Note, and 3 Noh-P.U.N.K. Ze Amin. We are not playing Ogre Dance because we don’t need to necessarily search or open a P.U.N.K. monster in specific. We are getting to Ze Amin off of Overdrive Teleporter for your whole P.U.N.K. combo either way. Foxy Tune can send itself and another card from hand to GY to Special Summon a P.U.N.K. monster from Deck except for a Level 8 monster. Deer Note can reveal itself and another P.U.N.K. monster in hand to Special Summon 1 of them and send the other to the GY. This does get a monster onto the field that you can Tribute to Tribute Summon Overdrive Teleporter, but you are going neg-1 if you do this and it hurts even more if you have to Small World to do anything with that hand also. But, we are mainly using Deer Note for its other effect which is that if it is sent from field to GY, you can target a P.U.N.K. monster in GY except for a Level 5 monster and Special Summon it. Ze Amin pays 600 LP to add a P.U.N.K. monster from Deck to hand and if it is sent to GY, you can target a P.U.N.K. monster you control to have it gain 600 ATk. This ATK gain effect is actually pretty useful for Chain Blocking either Deer Note or Dragon Drive. 3 Overdrive Teleporter which cannot be Special Summoned and can pay 2000 Life Points once while on field to Special Summon 2 Level 3 Psychic monsters from Deck. This card is miserable to set-up and it has a huge target on its back to be handtrapped, but you gotta do what you gotta do to make Overmind Archfiend. Finally, 2 Psychic Tracker which can be Special Summoned from hand as an inherent Summon if you control a Level 3 monster other than Tracker once per turn. And if it is used as Synchro Material, that monster gains 600 ATK. You are going to be using both Trackers in your combo, but you need at least 1 in Deck to get off of Overdrive Teleporter.

Spell/Traps: 1 Instant Fusion for Master of Ham and you can also use that Master of Ham to Tribute Summon Overdrive Teleporter. 3 Underworld Ritual of Prediction which Ritual Summons a Prediction Princess Ritual Monster from hand or GY face-up or face-down and you can banish it from GY during the Standby Phase to Special Summon a non-Ritual Prediction Princess from Deck face-down. 2 Prediction Ritual which specifically Ritual Summons Prediction Princess Tarotrei and you can banish it from GY except during the turn it was sent there in order to search for a Prediction Princess monster. 3 Pre-Preparation of Rites. 3 Small World. 3 Pot of Prosperity. 3 World Legacy Monstrosity which either Special Summons a Level 9 monster from hand or targets a Level 9 monster you control to Special Summon 2 Level 9 monsters from your Deck with a different Type and Attribute but with different names. Finally, 3 Emergency Teleport which Special Summons a Level 3 or lower Psychic monster from Deck, banishing it during the End Phase. 

Extra Deck: 1 Master of Ham which Special Summons a Flip Monster from hand or Deck face-down on Fusion Summon. 1 Cloudcastle which Special Summons a Level 9 monster from GY on Synchro Summon. 1 Overmind Archfiend. 1 P.U.N.K. JAM Dragon Drive which, if Synchro Summoned or Special Summoned by the effect of a P.U.N.K. card, you can pay 600 LP to take a Level 3 Psychic monster from Deck and either add it to hand or send it to GY. And if your opponent activates a card or effect in response to your P.U.N.K. card or effect activation, you can Special Summon it from GY. 2 Herald of the Arc Light which searches a Ritual Monster or Ritual Spell from Deck if sent to GY. 2 Mereologic Aggregator. 1 Laevateinn, Generaider Boss of Shadows and 1 Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity. 1 Underworld Goddess of the Closed World. 1 Sky Strike Ace - Camellia. 1 S:P Little Knight. 1 I:P Masquerena. And 1 Gravity Controller. 

Side Deck: 2 Nibiru, the Primal Being, 3 Thunder King, the Lightningstrike Kaiju, 2 Gizmek Kaku, the Supreme Shining Sky Stag, 3 Dark Ruler No More, 2 Lightning Storm, and 3 Evenly Matched.

The Level 9 monster that we are looking at today is one of my favorite Weather Painter cards,  Metaltron XII, the True Dracombatant. It is a Level 9 LIGHT Wyrm monster that requires 3 Tributes to Normal Summon it, being unable to be Normal Set. You can also Tribute Continuous Spell/Trap Cards you control to Tribute Summon this card in addition to monsters and it is unaffected by effects of cards with the same card type (Monster, Spell, and/or Trap) as the original card types of the cards used to Tribute Summon this card. And if it is Tribute Summoned and destroyed by your opponent’s card by battle or effect, you can Special Summon a Fusion, Synchro, or Xyz Monster from your Extra Deck that is EARTH, WATER, FIRE, or WIND Attribute. Metaltron is a pretty bad card in reality when you place it right next to Master Peace, the True Dracoslaying King. Being a 3 Tribute monster that floats into an Extra Deck monster if your opponent destroys it just doesn’t compare to a 2-Tribute monster that has the same protection (albeit from two card types rather than three) that acts as removal on both player’s turns. Since we aren’t playing actual True Draco, the Deck can be pretty inconsistent at times, considering that Dragonic Diagram is Limited. It is not great, but full combo is Dreiath III, the True Dracocavalry General, a True Draco Continuous Spell, World Legacy Monstrosity, and a way to get another monster on the field. We are playing the Deep Sea Diva and Guitar Gurnards Duonigis package in order to access Synchro plays. And with Gurnards being able to double the Level of a WATER you control, you have access to a suite of Synchros like Accel Synchro Stardust Dragon which can get you to Baronne de Fleur, Yazi, Evil of the Yang Zing, White Aura Whale, and other cool Synchros. And while we are playing Yazi and White Aura Whale, with Ib the World Chalice Justiciar being newly Limited, Diva and Gurnards can easily make her to search for Monstrosity which checks off 2 of your required pieces in your combo being Monstrosity and a monster on field. So, if you do draw Diva, that narrows your combo down to Diva, Dreiath, and a True Draco Continuous Spell. Normal Summon Diva, Special Summon Gurnards from Deck, Synchro in to Ib, and Ib searches for Monstrosity. Activate the True Draco Continuous Spell and use its immediate Normal Summon to Tribute the Continuous Spell to Tribute Summon Dreiath. Link Dreiath and Ib into some Link Monster, trigger Dreiath to Special Summon Metaltron XII from Deck, and activate Monstrosity targeting Metaltron XII for full Prediction Princess combo. Can you just hard Summon Metaltron XII? Yes, you really can. All it requires is a True Draco Continuous Spell and 3-material worth of Tribute for Metaltron XII and Monstrosity. So, that usually translates to Diva, 2 True Draco Continuous Spells, and Metaltron XII, but you really do have to play around with your hand to see where you are able to go. The combo I described is just a suggestion. Unlike some of my other Prediction Princess Decks, you can’t really just draw combo. You have to tinker with your hand until you get where you need to go. This Deck is just okay. Biggest downside is your inability to search for your True Draco cards, specifically your True Draco monsters. It’s not like we can play Majesty Maiden, the True Dracocaster or Swordsoul Emergence to get a Wyrm from Deck, and with Diagram at 1, it really does show the inconsistency of True Draco when you are not playing an actual True Draco Deck with draw Spells. 

For the Main Deck monsters: 3 Prediction Princess Traotrei, 1 Prediction Princess Tarotreith, and 3 Prediction Princess Bibliomuse. Tarotrei can Quick Effect flip a monster on field face-up or face-down and during your End Phase, she can Special Summon a Flip Monster from hand or GY face-down. Tarotreith must either be Ritual Summoned or Special Summoned via Tarotrei’s End Phase effect. Her Flip Effect Special Summons a Flip Monster from your Deck face-down and she can also Quick Effect flip any number of your monsters face-up or face-down. Bibliomuse can Special Summon herself back from the GY face-down if she is Tributed and sent there. Her Flip Effect adds a Prediction Princess monster other than herself and a Ritual Spell from your Deck to your hand and while she is face-up on the field, your Ritual Monsters gain targeting and destruction protection from your opponent’s effects. 2 Deus-X Krawler which negates all activated monster effects on your opponent’s side of the field after it has been flipped face-up and if it is destroyed on field, you can search for a Level 9 monster with a different Type and Attribute than it. 2 Metaltron XII, the True Dracombatant. You could play the 1 copy, but Dreiath only Summons from Deck and hard drawing it isn't too bad either. 3 Dreiath III, the True Dracocavalry General. It can also be Tribute Summoned using Continuous Spell/Traps you control. It prevents your opponent frmo targeting face-up True Draco and True King monsters on the field with card effects and they also cannot be destroyed by their card effects either. And if it is Tribute Summoned and leaves the field, you an Special Summon a True King or True Draco monster from Deck in Defense. 1 Guitar Gurnards Duonigis. On Special Summon, it banishes cards from the top of your opponent's Deck equal to the number of WATER monsters you control. Can't really see this doing much unless you banish a card your opponent wants to keep in Deck and it is not like we are playing Deep Sea Prima Donna either to really make use of the banishes. Just don't activate this against Kashtira. Also, you can target a Level 4 or lower WATER monster you control and increase its Level by its orignal Level which really helps out with getting you to a variety of Synchro plays. 3 Deep Sea Diva which Special Summons a Level 3 or lower Sea Serpent monster from Deck on Normal Summon.

Spell/Traps: 1 Terraforming. 1 Dragonic Diagram which can pop another card you control or in your hand to search for a True Draco or True King card from Deck. 3 True Draco Heritage which allows you to draw cards equal to the number of True King and True Draco card types that were sent from field to GY this turn. It doesn't do much if you activated or are going to activate Pot of Prosperity, but the most important part of this card is the immediate Normal Summon of a True King or True Draco monster which is considered as an additional Normal Summon. And if it is sent from the Spell/Trap Zone to Gy you can target and destroy a Spell/Trap on field. 3 Disciples of the True Dracophoenix. It can target 3 True Draco and/or True King cards in GY and shuffle them into the Deck to draw a card. It has the same immediate Normal Summon effect as Heritage. And if it is sent from the Spell/Trap Zone to the GY, you can target and destroy a Spell/Trap on field. 1 Instant Fusion for Master of Ham. 3 Pot of Prosperity. 3 Underworld Ritual of Prediction which Ritual Summons a Prediction Princess Ritual Monster from hand or GY face-up or face-down and you an banish it from GY during the Standby Phase to Special Summon a non-Ritual Prediction Princess monster from Deck. 3 World Legacy Monstrosity which either Special Summons a Level 9 monster from hand or targets a Level 9 monster you control to Special Summon 2 Level 9 monsters from Deck with a different Type and Attribute than it but with different names. 3 Infinite Impermanence. 1 True King's Return which targets and destroys a monster on field if it is sent from the Spell/Trap Zone to GY. You can target a True King or True Draco monster in your GY and Special Summon it in Defense Position but you cannot special Summon for the rest of the turn. Also, during your opponent's Main Phase, you can Immediately Tribute Summon a True Draco or True King monster face-up.

Extra Deck: 1 Master of Ham which can Special Summon a Flip Monster from Deck face-down on Fusion Summon. 1 White Aura Whale which needs a Water Tuner and non-Water monsters for material which is easily fulfilled by Diva and Gurnards. On Synchro Summon, it can destroy all Attack Position monsters your opponent controls, and it can declare 2 attacks on your opponent's monsters each Battle Phase, also dealing piercing damage. And if it destroyed by your opponent's card by battle or effect, you can banish another WATER from GY to Special Summon it from GY as a Tuner. 1 Yazi, Evil of the Yang Zing which can target a Yang Zing you control and a card your opponent controls and destroy them, and if it is destroyed by battle or card effect and sent to GY, you can Special Summon a Wyrm monster from Deck like Metaltron which gives you a way to pop an opponent's card and immediately get to a Level 9. 1 Ib the World Chalice Justiciar which adds a World Legacy card from Deck to hand on Synchro Summon. 2 Herald of the Arc Light which adds a Ritual Monster or Ritual Spell from Deck to hand if sent to GY. 1 Divine Arsenal AA-ZEUS - Sky Thunder. 2 Mereologic Aggregator. 1 Laevateinn, Generaider Boss of Shadows and 1 Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity. 1 S:P Little Knight, 1 I:P Masquerena, 1 Donner, Dagger Fur Hire, and 1 Gravity Controller.

Side Deck: 2 Nibiru, the Primal Being, 3 Thunder King, the Lightningstrike Kaiju, 2 Gizmek Kaku, the Supreme Shining Sky Stag, 3 Dark Ruler No More, 2 Lightning Storm, and 3 Evenly Matched.

I have a 50% win rate against Icejade, but I've only played against the Deck twice to be fair and both times were in Master Duel. The first time my opponent hard opened Icejade Curse, Icejade Cenote Enion Cradle, Icejade Kosmochlor, and Maxx "C" like a literal divine cringe incarnate and the second time I was matched against the Deck, they literally bricked and imploded in on themselves. I don't particularly hate Icejade, but I just hate their playstyle. Their artwork is so cool and it all just devolves into stun. Icejade has 1 Level 9 monster and that is Icejade Creation Kingfisher. Kingfisher is a Level 9 WATER Aqua monster. It can target a WATER monster you control and equip itself from hand or field to it and if it is equipped to an Icejade monster, that monster can attack while in Defense Position, applying its DEF for damage calculation like a Superheavy Samurai does. Also while it is equipped, you can target a monster your opponent controls with ATK less then or equal to the equipped monster's DEF in order to Special Summon this card and return the targeted monster to hand. When I am doing these Level 9 experimentations with Prediction Princess, I really like it when the Level 9 monster that I am trying to work with has its own effect to Special Summon itself. Sometimes that effect isn't usable due to you not being able to set up the right conditions in order to fulfill the requirements necessary to Special Summon that card by its own effect. But luckily, we are actually able to fulfill the requirements for Kingfisher to Special Summon itself. We are going to be using our old friend Girsu, the Orcust Mekk-Knight in order to be going through a combo that sends World Legacy - "World Armor" from our Deck to the GY, make some Tokens on both fields, Link into Lib the World Key Blademaster, set World Legacy Succession from Deck, bring back World Armor, and search for World Legacy Monstrosity while setting up the requirements for Kingfisher to be Summoned in 2 different ways with Monstrosity access. We just need Girsu, the Orcust Mekk-Knight and Icejade Creation Kingfisher in hand or a way to add it from Deck or Special Summon it from Deck. You'd be adding it from Deck via Icejade Cradle and you will be able to Special Summon it from Deck with Icejade Manifestation. Normal Girsu and use its effect to send World Armor from Deck to GY. Activate Girsu's other effect since it is the only monster you control to Special Summon a World Legacy Token to both players' fields. Link Girsu and your Token into Lib the World Key Blademaster which we are able to do since World Armor is our World Legacy card in GY. Ib then sets World Legacy Succession from Deck and we are able to activate it since World Armor is in GY. Succession Special Summons back World Armor to Lib's Linkpoint. World Armor searches Monstrosity from Deck on Summon. Now, let's say that you drew Kingfisher or Cradle to search Kingfisher. Link Lib and World Armor into Ib the World Chalice Priestess. DO NOT activate Lib's GY effect. Now, equip Kingfisher from hand to Ib. Now activate Kingfisher's effect  while equipped to Special Summon itself and bounce your opponent's Token. Ib is a Link Monster with no DEF, so it is still possible to bounce a 0 DEF Token with Kingfisher. Activate Monstrosity targeting Kingfisher for Bibliomuse and Deus-X from Deck and you have full Prediction Princess combo. Now, if you have Manifestation, after you make Ib, activate Manifestaation. Manifestation Special Summons Kingfisher from Deck and you can now target it with Monstrosity and you know the rest. I will say that Icejade Prediction Princess is among one of the better Prediction Princess Decks that I have made. If I had anything to really dislike about this Deck, it would be having to use Girsu. It isn't as accessible as Red Resonator and the Predaplants, but we have to play Girsu to set up Kingfisher/Manifestation while also searching for Monstrosity. To circumvent the potential of not drawing Girsu, I am choosing to play Pre-Preparation of Rites and Prediction Ritual, but that is taking up our Deckslots to play nonengine cards. I mean, since Knightmare Mermaid is banned, this is the Deck that makes the best out of the whole Girsu into Lib line. And considering that we are playing Icejade Ran Aegirine, we can have some interesting plays. 

.For the Main Deck monsters: 3 Prediction Princess Traotrei, 1 Prediction Princess Tarotreith, and 3 Prediction Princess Bibliomuse. Tarotrei can Quick Effect flip a monster on field face-up or face-down and during your End Phase, she can Special Summon a Flip Monster from hand or GY face-down. Tarotreith must either be Ritual Summoned or Special Summoned via Tarotrei’s End Phase effect. Her Flip Effect Special Summons a Flip Monster from your Deck face-down and she can also Quick Effect flip any number of your monsters face-up or face-down. Bibliomuse can Special Summon herself back from the GY face-down if she is Tributed and sent there. Her Flip Effect adds a Prediction Princess monster other than herself and a Ritual Spell from your Deck to your hand and while she is face-up on the field, your Ritual Monsters gain targeting and destruction protection from your opponent’s effects. 2 Deus-X Krawler which negates all activated monster effects on your opponent’s side of the field after it has been flipped face-up and if it is destroyed on field, you can search for a Level 9 monster with a different Type and Attribute than it. 2 Icejade Creation Kingfisher. You could play 3, but unless you also draw Ran Aegirine, you can't really make use of the extra Kingfisher in hand if you draw multiple. 3 Icejade Ran Aegirine which can discard another Icejade or WATER monster to Summon itself and an Icejade Token (Aqua/WATER/Level 3/ATK 0/DEF 0) and while that Token is in the Monster Zone, you can't Summon from the Extra Deck except WATER monsters. Ran Aegirine is a Level 7 Tuner and with the Token being Level 3, you can access the Level 10 WATER Synchro pool which just consists of Swordsoul Supreme Sovereign - Chengying, Icejade Gymir Aegirine, and the new Lancea, Dragonic Ancestor of the Ice Spirit Mountain. Chengying is hard to out and it banishes a card from your opponent's field and GY when a card(s) is banished. Gymir Aegirine makes your face-up monsters unable to be destroyed or banished by your opponent's card effects and if you activated that in response to your opponent's card or effect, and your opponent has a card(s) with that name in their field or GY, you can banish those cards. And it can bring itself back from GY if a card(s) is banished by your opponent's card effect. Lancea can twice per turn, once per Chain, Special Summon an Ice Barrier monster from hand, Deck, Extra Deck, or GY if your opponent Special Summons a monster(s) and it can also float into an Ice Barrier Synchro, treating it as a Synchro Summon. Chengying is the best monster to Summon using Ran Aegirine since it is just a large, hard-to-out dude, who can also banish cards from field and GY. As for Gymir Aegirine and Lancea, they both have their downsides in this Deck. Gymir Aegirine isn't too useful in this Deck when we already have Bibliomuse protecting our Ritual Monsters which is enough for the most part. It's not like it gives your field targeting protection. Its protection is sort of limited in a sense as it can't protect you against Dark Ruler or Evenly which are the cards you are the most worried about facing in Prediction Princess. I feel like I we were to play a monster that gives protection or at least protects you from those threats, you could play something that covers those bases better or just play Whirlwind Weasel and shotgun its Flip Effect. I'm not saying you can't play it, but it doesn't help protect you against the things you are most worried about in this Deck. As for Lancea, it would be really good if we actually had field space for it. Like it can litereally Summon 2 floodgate Ice Barrier monsters with its effect and float into 3 banishes in Trishula, Zero Dragon of the Ice Barrier. We just do not have space on our field for what it can get us. 1 Icejade Tremora which can send itself from hand to Gy to Special Summon a WATER monster from hand and if a face-up WATER monster(s) you control is destroyed by batlte or card effect while it is in GY, you can banish it to Special Summon and Icejade from hand or GY except for Tremora. 1 World Legacy - "World Armor" which searches a World Legacy card from Deck on Normal or Special Summon. And 3 Girsu, the Orcust Mekk-Knight which sends an Orcust or World Legacy card from Deck to GY on Normal or Special Summon and if you control no other monsters, you can Special Summon a World Legacy Token to both players' field.

Spell/Traps: 1 Instant Fusion for Master of Ham. 2 Icejade Manifestation which if you control a WATER monster and your opponent has a monster on their field or in their GY, you can take an Icejade monster from Deck and either send it to GY or Special Summon it. And if a face-up Icejade monster you contorl leaves the field by your opponent's card effect except through being destroyed while Manifestation is in GY, you can banish this card to target a card your opponent controls and banish it. 3 Icejade Cradle which adds an Icejade monster from Deck to hand with a different name from the cards you control and in your GY. This card is not one per turn, so you can just keep searching Icejades you don't already have on field or in GY like Ran Aegirine for an additional piece of your endboard. 3 Pot of Prosperity. 2 World Legacy Monstrosity which either Special Summons a Level 9 monster from hand or targets a Level 9 monster you control to Special Summon 2 Level 9 monsters from Deck with a different Type and Attribute than it but with different names. 1 World Legacy Succession which Special Summons a monster from GY to Linkpoint. 3 Underworld Ritual of Prediction which Ritual Summons a Prediction Princess Ritual Monster from hand or GY face-up or face-down and you can banish it from GY during the Standby Phase to Special Summon a non-Ritual Prediction Princess from Deck face-down. 2 Prediction Ritual which specifically Ritual Summons Prediction Princess Tarotrei and you can banish it from GY except during the turn it was sent there in order to search for a Prediction Princess monster. 3 Pre-Preparation of Rites. And finally, 1 Called By the Grave. 

Extra Deck: 1 Master of Ham who can Special Summon a Flip Monster from hand or Deck face-down on Fusion Summon. 1 Swordsoul Supreme Sovereign  - Chengying. 1 Icejade Gymir Aegirine. 2 Herald of the Arc Light which searches a Ritual Monster or Ritual Spell from Deck if sent to GY. 1 Divine Arsenal AA-ZEUS - Sky Thunder. 2 Mereologic Aggregator. 1 Laevateinn, Generaider Boss of Shadows and 1 Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity. 1 Ib the World Chalice Priestess. 1 Lib the World Key Blademaster. 1 S:P Little Knight, 1 I:P Masquerena, and 1 Gravity Controller.

Side Deck: 3 Nibiru, the Primal Being, 3 Thunder King, the Lightningstrike Kaiju, 2 Gizmek Kaku, the Supreme Shining Sky Stag, 3 Dark Ruler No More, 1 Harpie's Feather Duster, and 3 Evenly Matched.

So, about a month ago, I've done a burning OTK with Fog Counters featuring Updraft. Yet, did you know you can also mill your opponent? Well, let's find out!

 

 

Gameplan

1) Discard Coltwing + Banisher with Ravenous and don't forget to hold Smoke Ball when it's time to combo. Meanwhile, play "Gift Exchange" and target on "Diamond-Dust Cyclone".

2) Place ME-PSY-YA on Pendulum Zone and Special Summon Black Luster Soldier (BLS) with its ability to unlock "Primal Seed" loop. Also, clear everything but BLS with "Offerings to the Doomed".

3) Revive Coltwing with "Monster Reborn" and replace it with a token by playing "Vertical Landing". By reviving Coltwing another time with "Monster Reborn", it should generate two more tokens.

4) The current level of Coltwing is based on the sum of level of tokens and original level of Coltwing. This is addition, which is actually done only by tokens, not setting its level to fixed amount. Therefore, by playing "Galaxy Queen's Light" on Coltwing, its level will increase with respect to level of tokens. Reason is that you will also increase the level of tokens. Here is the process:

  • At first, the level of Coltwing will be level 13 >>> Coltwing (4) + Token (3) + Token (3) + Token (3)
  • Galaxy Queen's Light >>> Target Coltwing (level 13) >>> Tokens will be level 13
  • New calculation = Token (13) + Token (13) + Token (13) + Coltwing (4) = Coltwing (43)

5) Repeat the step explained in #4, by targeting only on Coltwing and nothing else.

6) When you think it's enough or you couldn't play "Galaxy Queen's Light" due to limits, make enough space with Offerings and BLS to revive Ancient + Level 1 Non-Tuner + Level 1 Tuner with "Monster Reborn". Then, Synchro Summon Trishula with those three and start depleting your opponent's resources (Hand+Field+Graveyard) by banishing them. Repeat with "De-Synchro" until there is nothing left, especially in-hand.

7) After reviving a Level 1 Tuner with "Monster Reborn", Synchro Summon Baronne by using Trishula + Level 1 Tuner as materials. Next, revive Banisher with "Monster Reborn" and destroy ME-PSY-YA with Baronne. With Banisher around, everything will be sent to BZ, which is vital because you don't want your opponent to activate anything from GY.

8) Play "Cloudian Aerosol" by discarding Smoke Ball in-hand and targeting on BLS to let him carry tons of counters. Then, set Primal Seed + Drop Off and end your turn. Don't forget to change the button at the lower right corner of the screen into "ON" and you won't miss anything.

9) After giving your opponent "Diamond-Dust Cyclone" with "Gift Exchange" and activating "Drop Off" during your opponent's Draw Phase, your opponent will only have Cyclone. If your opponent activates the drawn card in response to "Drop Off", feel free to negate it with Baronne. Otherwise, you have two options to win...

  • Your opponent can activate Cyclone and end the misery by drawing lots of cards. BLS had lots of counters. For each 4 counters, your opponent draws a card, which is enough to deck-out, even with 60 cards deck.
  • Your opponent is stubborn to not activate. They can scoop, even before all of that happening. However, if they stay, fetch a monster from BZ with "Primal Seed" and Normal Summon it. Then, destroy it with Offerings to not let yourself deck-out and always set Drop Off to activate it during your opponent's Draw Phase. Meanwhile, revive beefy monsters with "Monster Reborn" and attack with all you got to kill the opponent.

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

deck_excerpt: Samsara Mill/Burn FTK ft. Maxx "C" + Trickstar Black Catbat
deck_description:
So, you might have heard of my Samsara decks: One of them focuses on Mill while another focuses on Burn. Here, I thought: Why not have best of both worlds?

 

 

Gameplan

1) Check these options before/during the game and change them as shown, which matters later on:

  • Self-Chain >>> On
  • Card Position >>> Manual
  • Activation Order Settings >>> On

2) At one point, play "Gift Exchange" and choose Maxx "C" as the target. Next, Synchro Summon Rockks by using Cthugua + Shamisen as materials and destroy Rockks with Ravenous to place Rockks on Pendulum Zone. Then, feel free to Synchro Summon Barrone with Ravenous + Level 1 Tuner as materials, if you wish.

3) Link Summon Saryuja but make sure you free up Main Monster Zones (MMZ) Saryuja points to your side. Place Guitariss on other Pendulum Zone and Pendulum Summon monsters, three of which have to be Hela + 2 x Trickstars placed on where Saryuja points to. Place Hela to the left and Trickstars to the center and right. Then, fill the rest via Pendulum Summon with any monsters but Samsara/Wattfox/Wanghu.

4) Link Summon Catbat by using 2 x Trickstars as materials and place Catbat to the center of Saryuja. Then, Special Summon Wanghu with Saryuja. If opposing side is full, clear with "Raigeki". Otherwise, pass Wanghu to your opponent with "Shien's Spy".

5) Play "Temple >>> Rebirth" combo and choose Types of monsters in GYs as Zombie, which synergizes well with Hela. Then, destroy all of your Spell/Trap cards with "Gryphon's Feather Duster", which is a must for Samsara to be always active during End Phase of yours...

  • Alternatively, you can also use "Twin Twisters", seen in "Side Deck". First, you can activate Pendulum Zone ability of Guitariss to return Guitariss + Rockks to your hand. Then, play "Twin Twisters" to destroy Temple + Rebirth. There, you don't control any Spell/Trap cards. This setup only matters if you don't want to reveal Samsara by discarding with "Into the Void" at End Phase, which also includes revealing Wattfox.

6) There is nothing else to do right now. So, if you have Wattfox + Samsara in-hand, jump into End Phase but not before changing the button at the lower right corner of the screen to "ON" to not miss anything...

  1. Change "Card Position" from "Manual" to "Auto" because there will be lots of Special Summoning and you don't want to waste any time with manual labor.
  2. Start by discarding your whole hand with "Into the Void". Then, use "Gift Exchange" to give your opponent Maxx "C".
  3. Activate Samsara to Special Summon it. There are two different outcomes, which will be in your favor:
    • If your opponent doesn't activate Maxx "C", they will be burned to the death by Catbat. Reason is that Wanghu will destroy Samsara, which is where Catbat points to. Then, Catbat deals damage because a monster (Samsara) this card points to has been destroyed.
    • Knowing that your opponent is scared of death, they can activate Maxx "C" and you may move onto next step.
  4. After the activation of Maxx "C", chain into Hela by tributing Hela and targeting Wattfox in GY to Special Summon it. Even though Wattfox isn't Zombie by default, "Rebirth Judgment" changed the outcome in that regard, so that Hela can be able to pick Wattfox.
  5. With Chain Link 3 ended, everything has been done in order. So, Wanghu will destroy Samsara and Wattfox. Samsara isn't important but Wanghu destroying Wattfox is a huge deal. Your opponent can't be able to activate anything to stop this Mill + Burn combo now.
  6. Since your opponent can't activate anything, that includes Wanghu destroying Samsara. Kindly return Wanghu to where it belongs by pressing the button of "Shien's Spy".
  7. Finally, you can Special Summon Samsara and Wanghu can destroy it. Meanwhile, your opponent draws one by one and takes damage, all thanks to Maxx "C" and Catbat. Repeat this process until your opponent is demolished...
    • If you wish, for convenience, you can change the button at the lower right corner of the screen to "OFF" and Activation Order Settings to "Off". Therefore, you will be always asked whether you want to Special Summon Samsara or not, without Baronne asking what to do.

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contract Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Rebirth Judgment" can be collected by purchasing "Cybernetic Successor" deck. 30 UR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Raigeki" is given for free, if you have completed the tutorial to save 30 UR!

- "Into The Void" + "Allure of Darkness" can be found within "The Infinite Void" Secret Pack to save 180 SR!

- "Ravenous" + "Pot of Acquisitiveness" + "Samsara Lotus" + "King Tiger Wanghu" + "Gift Exchange" can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 150 SR!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 660 SR and 150 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

deck_excerpt: Chaos Emperor Dragon OTK ft. Arcana + Gift Exchange + Ruddy + Necroface
deck_description:
(Credit to Rengetsu for decktesting! Thanks a bunch! Note that everything is done within 300 sec timer limit, just like how you would do in Ranked.)

Have you ever wondered how to relive old days of Chaos Emperor Dragon (CED)? Despite with harsh errata done on CED, with a lenghty setup and a patient opponent, you can just do so!

 

 

Gameplan

1) After discarding Necroface with Dugares/Ravenous, place ME-PSY-YA on Pendulum Zone. Then, Special Summon CED with its ability by banishing Necroface + Formula/Integrator to unlock "Primal Seed" loop.

2) If "Light Barrier" is present, Special Summon Arcana with Saryuja and choose the outcome as heads to always skip your opponent's turn at the cost of two of your monsters being delivered to GY. Meanwhile, activate "Infinite Cards" to not discard anything, which will matter later on.

3) Skip your Draw Phase with Dugares/Offerings. Next, set "Primal Seed" + "Gift Exchange". Then, destroy "Light Barrier" with Baronne and end your turn. Don't forget to skip your opponent's turn with Arcana.

4) With "Primal Seed" loop, fetch "Monster Reborn" + "Offerings to the Doomed" + "Necroface". Revive Ancient + Martial with "Monster Reborn" and bring forth Ruddy with these two to send everything from GY to BZ. Then, Normal Summon Necroface to shuffle everything from BZ into Main/Extra Deck.  You can destroy Necroface with Offerings to not draw a card, up to you.

5) Play "Gift Exchange" and target "Primal Seed" to keep the engine running. Then, target anything but Quick-Play spell cards with "Gift Exchange", until your opponent has nothing in Main Deck.

6) When the time has come, destroy ME-PSY-YA with Baronne and end your turn. First, use Arcana to skip your opponent's turn by sending Ruddy + Baronne to GY. Then, hold your opponent's cards with "Gift Exchange".

7) Finally, it's your turn. Activate CED to deal lethal damage.

deck_excerpt: Slash Draw FTK ft. Primal Seed + Yado + Angineer
deck_description:
Greetings! In this deck, we will FTK our opponent with "Slash Draw". Unlike other builds you might have seen around, this is really consistent to setup. All it takes is placing cards from your hand to bottom of your deck with Yado + Angineer duo.

 

 

Gameplan

1) When Baronne is around, Link Summon Saryuja. Then, place ME-PSY-YA on Pendulum Zone and Special Summon Chaos Emperor Dragon with its ability to unlock "Primal Seed" loop.

2) Thanks to monsters being revived by "Monster Reborn", XYZ Summon Angineer by using 2 x Level 3 monsters (Martial/Integrator/Shamisen) as materials. Then, Special Summon Yado with Saryuja in Attack Position. This is important, don't summon Yado in Defense Position.

3) Fill your opponent's side by reviving your monsters with "Monster Reborn" and passing monsters to them with "Shien's Spy". Meanwhile, empty your Main Deck completely by drawing everything and fill your side with "Monster Reborn" as well.

4) Activate Angineer and target on Yado to change it from Attack to Defense Position. Here, you can activate Yado and count down how many cards your opponent controls. If you have filled the opposing side and you went first, there should be 5. So, place any 5 cards but "Slash Draw" from your hand at the bottom of your Main Deck, one by one. Yado's ability is similar to Saryuja's. Then, place 6th and final one, which has to be "Slash Draw"...

  • Rather than Angineer, there are other cards which let you change Yado into Defense Position. You can check them in "Side Deck".

5) Destroy ME-PSY-YA with Baronne because game checks whether cards were sent into GY or not, if you play "Slash Draw". So, with that out of the way, activate "Slash Draw" for the massive FTK.

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contract Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Monster Reborn" is given for free, if you have completed the tutorial to save 30 UR!

- "Into The Void" + "Allure of Darkness" can be found within "The Infinite Void" Secret Pack to save 180 SR!

- "Formula Synchron" can be found within "Stardust Ties" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "Baronne de Fleur" can be found within "The Noble Knights of Crimson Flowers" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Number 60: Dugares the Timeless" can be found within "Number Recall" Secret Pack to save 30 SR!

- "T.G. Hyper Librarian" can be found within "Futuristic Creatures" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Moray of Avarice" can be found within "Treasures of the Cosmic Ocean" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Wonder Wand" and "Spellbook of Knowledge" can be collected by purchasing "Spellbook of Prophecy" deck. 120 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Ravenous" + "Pot of Acquisitiveness" + "Slash Draw" + "Primal Seed" can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 60 SR and 120 UR!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 510 SR and 240 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. Let me know if you have any questions and have fun in Master Duel!

deck_excerpt: Number 43 FTK ft. Cold Enchanter + Snow Dragon + King Tiger Wanghu
deck_description:
Well, seems like Number 43 has finally snapped. This fella is now an ice cold killer, be careful!

 

 

Gameplan

1) Plant the roses to opposing side with "Black Garden", if you go first. Then, send Number 13 to GY, either as Link Material for Saryuja or with Ravenous/Wok.

2) Send Wanghu + Enchanter + Snow to GY, which is possible with Ancient/Ravenous/Dugares. You have to send at least two of them and third one can be Special Summoned with Saryuja.

3) Place ME-PSY-YA on Pendulum Zone and Special Summon Chaos Emperor Dragon with its ability to unlock "Primal Seed" loop. Also, feel free to clear everything but Chaos Emperor with "Mystik Wok".

4) Revive Number 13 with "Monster Reborn" and overlay into Number 43 with "Rank-Up-Magic Launch". Place Number 43 on Extra Monster Zone (EMZ) for convenience.

5) Revive "Cold Enchanter" and you can start accumulating Ice Counters with its ability to boost its ATK. However, I have a better idea: Revive Wanghu >>> Snow in explained order. There, Wanghu destroys Snow and Snow triggers its ability to place Ice Counter on every face-up monster present.

6) Revive Snow as many times as you can, while placing Ice Counters everywhere and boosting the ATK of "Cold Enchanter". When the ATK of Enchanter is higher than your opponent's LP, activate "Mystik Wok" and target on Enchanter. By choosing its ATK, you will gain lots of LP. There, Number 43 will convert said amount as damage to kill your opponent.

deck_description: Jaden Yuki uses "Elemental Hero" Decks.
Deck usado pela Madoka no 2° torneio do Zona de Duelos de 14/01/2024
Deck Inicial do jogo The Eternal Duelist Soul

INTRODUCTION

Greetings! If you are looking at this deck, it means you are a fellow Treasure Panda player. Perhaps, you are also looking for how to guide "Treasure Panda" decks? Whatever your reason is, I'm willing to help you, with in-depth analysis of key cards and whatnot.

 

BASICS

- Treasure Panda decks rely on banishing Spell/Trap cards from your GY to Special Summon Normal Monster, ranging from Level 1 to 3. It's mostly used in conjuction with Level 1 monsters, so that you can do the following:

  1. Play "Upstart Goblin" or "Into the Void".
  2. Special Summon Level 1 monster.
  3. Target on that fella with "Wonder Wand" or any target spells to draw more cards.
  4. When you are out of Level 1 monsters, play "Pot of Avarice" and/or "Pot of Acquisitiveness" to refill your Main Deck.
  5. Repeat everything from the beginning.

- This is essential part of playing "Treasure Panda" decks. No matter what your plan is, you will repeat these steps above. However, there is still much to learn...

 

MAIN TOOLS

- Let's have a look at what we have. Then, we can check out alternative cards, whether it's due to crafting costs (SR/UR) or preferences...

  • T.G. Hyper Librarian: Most valuable player, ditto. Besides Treasure Panda, everything is centered around Librarian. Reason is that each time you Synchro Summon, you draw a card, and Treasure Panda decks utilize Synchro Summoning mechanics a lot. You can check this Synchro Summon hierarchy to see what I mean...

    1. If you open up with Monk >>> Panda, this is how you can play with...

      • Assuming that you have always spells to draw, this is how: Monk + Tuner = Librarian >>> Tuner + Non-Tuner = Formula >>> Formula + Non-Tuner = Martial >>> Martial brings Formula >>> Formula + Non-Tuner = Integrator >>> Martial + Integrator = Stardust >>> Stardust (Tuner due to Martial) + Non-Tuner = Ancient >>> Ancient pulls Level 1 Tuner >>> Ancient + Tuner = Accel >>> Accel pulls Formula >>> Formula + Non-Tuner = Shamisen >>> Shamisen + Non-Tuner = Cthugua >>> Bring Shamisen back onto the battlefield and shuffle Formula >>> Shamisen + Non-Tuner = Cthugua >>> Cthugua + Cthugua = Number 60 >>> Draw four cards with Number 40! >>> Accel + Tuner = Ravenous >>> Saryuja

    2. If you start only with Panda, this is how you can play with:

      • Tuner + Non-Tuner = Formula >>> Formula + Non-Tuner = Martial >>> Martial brings Formula >>> Formula + Non-Tuner = Integrator >>> Martial + Integrator = Stardust >>> Stardust (Tuner due to Martial) + Non-Tuner = Ancient >>> Ancient pulls Monk/Panda >>> Monk/Panda + Tuner = Librarian >>> Ancient + Tuner = Accel >>> Accel pulls Formula >>> Formula + Non-Tuner = Shamisen >>> Shamisen + Non-Tuner = Cthugua >>> Bring Shamisen back onto the battlefield and shuffle Formula >>> Shamisen + Non-Tuner = Cthugua >>> Cthugua + Cthugua = Number 60 >>> Draw four cards with Number 40! >>> Accel + Tuner = Ravenous >>> Saryuja
  • Summoner Monk: If you don't open with Panda, you can play Monk to pull Panda from your Main Deck by discarding a spell.
  • Upstart Goblin / Into the Void / Allure of Darkness: Your openers when Panda is present, so that you can start pulling out Level 1 dudes.
  • Wonder Wand / Spellbook of Knowledge / White Elephant's Gift / Moray of Avarice: When you have pulled out Level 1 dude with Panda, you can use your target spells to draw 2 cards.
  • Pot of Acquisitiveness: Since "Allure of Darkness" and "Moray of Avarice" draw cards while banishing, if you hit Level 1 dudes, you can recover them with this Pot card.
  • Pot of Avarice: Whenever you are out of resources when it comes to Level 1 monsters, don't forget to play this Pot.
  • Magical Mallet / Reload: If you brick, use these cards to find a way out.
  • Formula / Integrator / Stardust / Ravenous: Your draw abilities as Synchros.
  • Martial / Shamisen / Ancient / Accel: Your extenders as Synchros. It means they Special Summon extra bodies or themselves with their abilities. Feel free to check Synchro Summon hierarchy explained in Librarian part to see what I mean.
  • Number 60: Your draw ability as XYZ. Thanks to 2 x Cthuguas present, you can overlay into Number 60 and draw up to 4 cards! Pretty cool, isn't it? Depending on your plan, feel free to use its Special Summon ability.
  • Saryuja: Your draw ability as Link. Better used when you have 4 cards in Main Deck since Saryuja lets you draw 4 cards, if you use 4 materials for Saryuja. Even though you have to shuffle back three cards in the end, that concludes your drawing session. Depending on your plan, feel free to use its Special Summon ability.

 

SIDE TOOLS

- Here are your optional cards, where you can substitute them:

  • Cup of Ace: "Pot of Greed" with a gamble. Either you or your opponent draws 2 cards. It's similar to "Allure of Darkness" but you can let your opponent draw cards with "Cup of Ace". With Allure, you either draw or lose everything, without giving your opponent anything.
  • One Day of Peace / Dark World Dealings / Hand Destruction / Fortune Fairy Chee: These cards allow both sides to draw.
  • Fragrance Storm: A conditional "Wonder Wand", literally. You target a Level 1 Plant to destroy it and draw a card. However, if you want to draw 2, your first draw has to be a Plant. If you replace Level 1 Spellcasters (Exodias/Idol) with Level 1 Plant monsters, replace 3 x Wonder Wand + 1 x Spellbook of Knowledge with 3 x Fragrance Storm.
  • Moray of Greed: If you add this card, you need to replace Level 1 Spellcasters with Level 1 Water monsters. I think 8 x Level 1 Water monsters with 2 x Moray of Greed in mind is fair but proceed with caution.
  • Where Arf Thou?: This helps you tutor Level 1 monsters, which can harmonize well with "Moray of Greed", if you choose that path. I guess 1-2 copies shall suffice but consider with caution.
  • Spellbook of Secrets: You can tutor "Spellbook of Knowledge" with this card. 1 x Secrets is enough.
  • Spellbook of the Master: If you haven't banished "Spellbook of Knowledge" with Panda but want to use Knowledge another time to draw 2 more cards, Master can help you out. 1 x Master is enough.
  • Advance Draw: Since Accel and Ravenous sit idle after they were used, you can Tribute them to draw 2 cards. As you can see, 1 x Advance Draw is enough.
  • Celestial Observatory / Sacred Sword of Seven Stars / Trade-In / Kuji-Kiri Curse / Tokusano Shinkyojin: Similar to "Advance Draw", if your setup allows to, you can add these cards to to target Level 6-7-8-9-10 cards and draw accordingly. Just be mindful of hard/soft once per turn rulings.
  • Gold Moon Coin: To draw 2 cards, you have to give your opponent 2 cards of yours.
  • Monster Recovery + Link Bound: If you feel like crafting whole Extra Deck can break the bank, just craft Saryuja and add these two spells. Since the draw effect of Saryuja isn't hard once per turn, you can return Saryuja with these cards to Extra Deck and try again. Feel free to replace one copy of "Reload" with "Monster Recovery" and only add 1 x Link Bound, see how it goes.
  • Anchamoufrite: If you have removed every card in Extra Deck but Saryuja, consider adding 1 x Anchamoufrite. When Saryuja is present, you can use its Pendulum ability to draw a card, since your Extra Deck has 0 cards anyways.
  • Performapal Guitartle + Performapal Lizardraw: Alternative Pendulum duo, which draws cards like Anchamoufrite. First, activate Guitartle. Then, activate Lizardraw. Here, Guitartle draws a card and then, you can destroy Lizardraw to draw another card.
  • Link Spider: If your Extra Deck has only Saryuja, this spider can alleviate your overload by pulling out 1 x Normal Monster from your hand, which enables you to play target spells such as "Wonder Wand". 1 x Link Spider is enough because it's hard-once per turn.
  • Cards of Consonance: "Flamvell Guard" is a Dragon Tuner with 100 ATK, which fits the criteria for "Cards of Consonance". If you don't want to craft "Moray of Avarice" since it's UR, consider replacing "Water Spirit" cards with "Flamvell Guard" and add 1-2 x Consonance.
  • Soul Absorption + Ancient Leaf: This duo work well in harmony. Reason is that, as you banish spells with Panda, you will gain 500 LP for each. When you have 9000+ LP, you pay 2000 LP to draw 2 cards. If your setup relies on banishing stuff for gaining LP, this duo is amazing to have but only if you lack some cards.
  • Tilted Try / Chicken Game: Field Spells which help you draw cards. If the setup you made doesn't require you to burn your opponent to death, 3 x Chicken Game is alright to have. As for "Tilted Try", it acts like this: Let's say you have drawn card(s) with "Upstart Goblin" and/or "Wonder Wand" but you didn't like the results. Here, you can activate "Tilted Try" to shuffle one of drawn cards to bottom of your deck and then you draw a card. After it, "Tilted Try" will be detonated, which means a free resource for Panda and thinning your deck.
  • Daigusto Emeral: A mini Pot of Avarice, alternative to Dugares.
  • Mannadium Trisukta: Alternative to Accel, since Accel is UR to craft. What Accel did was to Special Summon Level 2 Tuner and Trisukta does no different. However, you have to replace it with "Stardust Charge Warrior".
  • Coral Dragon: Alternative to "Stardust Charge Warrior", Coral does what Stardust do: Draw a card.
  • Toon Table of Contents + Toon Bookmark: Tutor cards which fetch Toon cards from your deck to your hand. To thin your deck, here is an example of Toon package but feel free to refer this page to make a setup of your own: 3 x Toon Table of Contents >>> 1 x Toon Bookmark >>> 1 x Blue-Eyes Toon Dragon >>> 1 x Trade-In.
  • Card of Fate: Draw a random card from your Main Deck. May RNG be with you and 1 x Card of Fate is enough.
  • Synchro Creed: You can add 1 x Synchro Creed to draw card(s), assuming you control Synchro monster(s). If you control 1 x Synchro, you draw 1 card. If you control 3+ Synchros, you can draw 2 cards.
  • Performage Hat Tricker: If you consider Summoner Monk as expensive to craft (SR) but still want to bring forth Librarian easily, might I suggest Hat Tricker? You can Special Summon it as many times as you want, as long as there are 2+ monsters on the field. Also, since it's Spellcaster, you can target it with "Wonder Wand" and "Spellbook of Knowledge".
  • Pot of Greed / Graceful Charity / Terraforming: These are banned cards, which help you draw cards. Yet, I just wanted to mention them.

 

CONCLUSION

So, that's all for this guide. Let me know what you think or how we can improve this guide. Any feedback/suggestion is greatly appreciated. I tried my best to cover everything but let me know if I have missed anything, be it for substitutes or whatever. Have fun in Master Duel!
