deck_excerpt: The most consistent Ghoti Coelacanth deck
deck_description:
With Coelacanth you can summon a lot of monsters and do a lot of synchros, this way you can create a strong board at the first turn, and break the opponent's board at the second turn, while also creating a good board. This deck guarantees that you have the cards to summon Coelacanth at your first turn 70% of the time.

The main ways of summoning Coelacanth are:

  • Summon Lifeless, together with another lvl 4 or Reptolphin, use its effect to send Coelacanth to the GY, summon Dugares or Monoceros at the extra monster zone, and reborn Coelacanth with their effect
  • Use Tremora's or Paces's effect to summon Coelacanth from the hand
  • Summon two water monsters, then summon Abyss Keeper, and use its effect to summon Coelacanth from the hand
  • Use Lifeless to send Coelacanth to the GY and reborn it with Monster Reborn
  • Special-summon 2 monsters to tribute-summon Coelacanth from the hand the old way

The best combos occur when you have another fish together with Coelacanth (Monoceros, Abyss Keeper, or another random fish that can be normal or special-summoned from the hand throughout the combo), so that you can tribute it to negate any counter that targets Coelacanth. And always remember that you have to leave one card in the hand for Coelacanth's effect.

You can use some cards to search the deck for what you want:

  • One For One searches for Beautunaful
  • Beautunaful searches for Lifeless or Paces
  • Small World searches for any monster using almost any other monster from the hand and Gameciel from the deck

Going First

After summoning Coelacanth, if you didn't summoned it using Monoceros, you can:

  • Use Coelacanth's effect to bring Lifeless, Beautunaful, Paces/Shif and Reptolphin
  • Summon Baronne with Lifeless, Beautunaful and the lvl 2 Ghoti
  • If you have Dugares or Abyss Keeper at the board, pop them with Baronne's first effect (I know this doesn't feel right, but I didn't found another easier way to get them out of the way)
  • Summon Monoceros at the extra monster zone, using Lifeless and Reptolphin
  • Reborn Coelacanth with Monoceros' effect
  • Use Lifeless' effect at the GY to put back Reptolphin and 2 other fishes at your deck, and draw a card
  • Use Coelacanth's effect again to bring Reptolphin, Beautunaful and Paces/Shif
  • Use a lvl 7, Beautunaful and the lvl 2 Ghoti to make Chengying
  • Use a lvl 7 and Reptolphin to make Gymir, and buff it with Reptolphin's effect

If you used Monoceros to summon it at the first time, you just need to summon a lvl 4 fish instead of Reptolphin, and use it and Lifeless to summon Dugares to reborn Coelacanth the second time, then pop Dugares right after that.

At the end you will have 3 lvl 10 synchros: Baronne, Gymir and Chengying, that can negate an effect, banish cards from the field and the grave, and make your monsters immune to destruction and banishment.

You can also focus on Ghoti combos, keeping the board ready for a Deep Beyond in the next turn, while also summoning an Askaan, that can come back from the banishment after Deep Beyond's effect, and getting a Snopios from the deck

  • TODO

Going Second

This deck is not so good going second, but you can always use hand traps to stop opponent's combos on the first turn, and use Gameciel to get anoying monsters out of the way on your turn.

If you don't have any non-water monster at the GY, you can increment the main combo this way:

  • Use Coelacanth's effect to bring Lifeless, Beautunaful, Fishborg and Reptolphin
  • Summon Trishula with Coelacanth, Beautunaful and Fishborg, or a lvl 8 (White Aura Whale or Askaan) with Coelacanth and Fishborg
  • Bring back Fishborg from the GY
  • Summon Baronne with Trishula and Fishborg, or lvl 8, Beautunaful and Fishborg
  • Make the rest of the combo normally

You can also use Coral Anemone with Zealantis to clear the board

  • TODO

With Dimension Shifter

Dimension shifter is a strong card to catch the opponent off guard and prevent them from building a strong board, but you also have to deal with it on your turn.

In this situation you can only use combos that summon Coelacanth from the hand, since it will be banished if you send it to the GY. Also, you can only use its effect one time, since it will also be banished after being used as material.

After summoning it from the hand, you can:

  • Use Coelacanth's effect to bring two lvl 4 fishes, Paces/Shif and Reptolphin
  • Use them to summon two lvl 10 synchro monsters of your choice

You can also substitute the Reptolphin with a Fishborg to summon White Aura Whale instead, banishing the opponent's board.

If the opponent negates your effects

Most of the time you will have at least two lvl 4 monsters on the field. You can use them to summon a Bahamut Shark, together with Toadally Awesome, so you'll have some interaction next turn.

Sometimes you will have a way to feint:

  • Summon Lifeless and use its effect while already having Tremora and Coelacanth on the hand (send Shif to the GY, so you will have some interaction next turn if something else happens)
  • Use Small World while having all the cards you need on the hand (if the opponent don't counter, you can always get from the deck the same monster you banished from your hand)

Another interesting cards

Virtual World Kyubi - Shenshen: Can substitute a lvl 10 synchro, leaving behind a banish effect that is as anyoing for your opponent as Dimension Shifter after you already set up your board. Though it is an easy prey for Kaijus, Lava Golems, and cards like that, you can bring it back from the GY next turn.

Virtual World Beast - Jiujiu: Can act like a Snopios, banishing Shif and Paces from the GY to get a Deep Beyond next turn, while also being indestructable, since most of your cards are water and fish and you'll have a bunch of them at you GY after a Coelacanth combo.

Number 4: Stealth Kragen: Can prevent the opponent from doing actions that require specific attributes, can destroy opponent's monsters, inflicting damage to them, and can be reborn using a Stealth Kragen Spawn if you want. They can substitute Bahamut Shark and Toadally Awesome, or can work with them creating a new combo that summons lvl 4 xyzs instead of summoning lvl 10 synchros.

Abyss Dweller: Can give 500 atk for all your monsters (since they are all water) and also negate GY effects the next turn, which can be a really bad thing depending on the opponent's deck.

Red-Eyes Flare Metal Dragon: Can be summoned using Coelacanth and Monoceros, cannot be destroyed by card effects (since you will not detach materials from it anyway) and has an anoying effect that inflicts damage to the opponent every time they activate an effect.

deck_excerpt: When machines take over the world
deck_description: This deck is still under testing and surprised that it works well I think if I even it out a bit with some hand traps and maybe some lightsworn cards
Dragons

The only correct way to play Mannadium atm. I'm not sure if people are scared to play turn skip turbo but it's objectively the best version, easily. Yes you run many balls. Deck plays around ash, droll, imperm and veiler beautifully. But Nibiru is a problem. Little knight can help tho.

Gist of the deck:

Any way to a level 4 and a ball + anyway to visas= Beatrice + Baronne. Most hands (79%)you only have to search once. To achieve this.

If you don't open the above or get interupted, you just pivot to standard manna combo (Baronne + dis pater +apollusa/Little Knight).

With both lines you would still have 2-3 cards in hand after.

Fenrir doubles as extension and a going second card. That's why I'm fine running just 6 non engine game 1.

Funny synergy with Psychic End punisher, as the deck makes it pretty easily and after you rollback you'll always have 4000 LP or less, meaning psychic End punisher will be unaffected at 7500 ATK minimum.

Follow up is handicapped if you do go the Beatrice route, so you need many OTK options (Psychic End Punisher, astraloud, Accesscode)

Please don't question the number of balls, just run some test hands, you'll see they are necessary going first. Going second however is where this deck become very flexible because you can side out all torrid, 1 visas, 1 tear planet, 2 imaginings + the Beatrice Traps and you free up NINE slots for non engine, while maintaining combo consistency.

deck_excerpt: Extox Hydra Mill ft. Card Destruction
deck_description:
(Disclaimer: Card draw effect of Extox isn't mandatory. It's up to your opponent to activate. If they are adamant, just punch them into face with Limiter Removal next turn.)

Hello and welcome to another deck guide, where I will show you how to mill your opponent with "Extox Hydra" + "Card Destruction" combinations. Combined with "Limiter Removal" + "Reprodocus" duo, you can either mill them or punch them outright. The choice is up to your opponent and you can reply them accordingly. So, let's see...

 

 

Gameplan

1) At one point, place Librarian on Main Monster Zone (MMZ) and not Extra Monster Zone (EMZ). Then, discard Generator + Coltwing with Ravenous.

2) If you haven't Link Summoned Saryuja, Link Summon "Proxy F Magician" by using EMZ + Shamisen as materials. Then, Fusion Summon Extox by using Magician + Librarian as materials...

  • However, if you have Link Summoned Saryuja, Special Summon Arcana with Saryuja. By the way, don't use Librarian as Link Material for Saryuja. Then, Link Summon Magician with Arcana + Saryuja and Fusion Summon Extox with Magician + Librarian.

3) Place ME-PSY-YA on Pendulum Zone and Special Summon Black Luster Soldier (BLS) at anywhere but behind the EMZ with his ability to unlock "Primal Seed" loop. Next, Link Summon Saryuja and Special Summon Arcana with Saryuja. Then, Link Summon Reprodocus by using Arcana + Saryuja as materials.

4) Clear everything but BLS + Reprodocus with "Offerings to the Doomed", if you must. Then, revive Coltwing with "Monster Reborn" and replace it with a token by playing "Vertical Landing". By reviving Coltwing another time with "Monster Reborn", it should generate two more tokens.

5) The current level of Coltwing is based on the sum of level of tokens and original level of Coltwing. This is addition, which is actually done only by tokens, not setting its level to fixed amount. Therefore, by playing "Galaxy Queen's Light" on Coltwing, its level will increase with respect to level of tokens. Reason is that you will also increase the level of tokens. Here is the process:

  • At first, the level of Coltwing will be level 13 >>> Coltwing (4) + Token (3) + Token (3) + Token (3)
  • Galaxy Queen's Light >>> Target Coltwing (level 13) >>> Tokens will be level 13
  • New calculation = Token (13) + Token (13) + Token (13) + Coltwing (4) = Coltwing (43)

6) Repeat the step explained in #5, by targeting only on Coltwing and nothing else. When you think it's enough or you couldn't play "Galaxy Queen's Light" due to limits, make enough space with Offerings and BLS by getting rid of tokens to revive Generator + Arcana but not before placing "Light Barrier" on the field to choose the outcome of Arcana. After choosing the outcome as heads to skip your opponent's turn at the cost of sending two of your monsters to GY at End Phase, use Generator to gain lots of LP by targeting either on Black Luster Soldier or Coltwing.

7) If you have played "Into the Void" while holding Zero King Rage, set "Primal Seed" + "Card Destruction" and end your turn. You can also set other combo pieces such as "Limiter Removal" + Offerings + Reborn + "Shien's Spy", up to you. Also, don't forget to skip your opponent's turn with Arcana by delivering Generator + Coltwing to GY.

8) It's your turn. Revive Zero King Rage and two other monsters. These monsters will be used as tribute for Zero King Rage to shut down your opponent's Hand + Backrow + GY. There will be no interruptions, be it for Evenly Matched or something else. Passing Zero King Rage to the opponent "Shien's Spy" doesn't change anything, either. So, why not give it to them?

9) Revive Extox, in Attack Position, right behind Reprodocus. There, change its Type to Machine. You can boost its ATK with "Limiter Removal" but there is a catch: Count how many cards your opponent has in their Main Deck and multiply it by 1000. My opponent started with 40 card Main Deck and at that time, they had 35 cards in their Main Deck. So, the ATK of Extox must be lower than 35000 and therefore, play "Limiter Removal" accordingly.

10) When the ATK of Extox reached to 32000, pass Extox to opposing side with "Shien's Spy". So far, there should be 3 x MMZ free. Refill them with Level 1 dudes and place them in Attack Position.

11) Jump into Battle Phase and attack Extox with Level 1 dudes. Here, you have two options...

  • If your opponent activates Extox, they will draw lots of cards, almost depleting their Main Deck. In that case, jump into Main Phase 2 and play "Card Destruction" to completely deck-out your opponent and win the game.
  • If your opponent is stubborn to not activate Extox, skip your opponent's turn with Arcana. Use Zero King Rage to shut down whatever your opponent has and boost Extox with what was explained in #9 to beat your opponent's ass.

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contract Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Black Luster Soldier - Envoy of the Beginning" can be collected by purchasing "Spiral Spear Strike" deck. 30 UR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Monster Reborn" is given for free, if you have completed the tutorial to save 30 UR!

- "Into The Void" + "Allure of Darkness" can be found within "The Infinite Void" Secret Pack to save 180 SR!

- "Arcana Force XXI - The World" + "Light Barrier" can be found within "Hand of Fate" Secret Pack to save 30 SR and 30 UR!

- "Formula Synchron" can be found within "Stardust Ties" Secret Pack to save 90 SR!

- "Baronne de Fleur" can be found within "The Noble Knights of Crimson Flowers" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "T.G. Hyper Librarian" can be found within "Futuristic Creatures" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Limiter Removal" can be found within "Roid Nexus" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Moray of Avarice" can be found within "Treasures of the Cosmic Ocean" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Wonder Wand" and "Spellbook of Knowledge" can be collected by purchasing "Spellbook of Prophecy" deck. 120 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Ravenous" + "Pot of Acquisitiveness" + "Zero King Rage" + "Card Destruction" + "Primal Seed" can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 90 SR and 90 UR!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 600 SR and 300 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. Let me know if you have any questions and have fun in Master Duel!
Gandalf Burn
